summary: Unusuall objects in the sky over Blacksburg, VA
stats: Occurred : 9/27/2019 08:40  (Entered as : 9-27-19 8:40) Reported: 10/10/2019 12:31:03 PM 12:31 Posted: 12/1/2019 Location: Blacksburg, VA Shape: Other Duration: 5 minutes Characteristics: There were lights on the object, There were aircraft in the vicinity or aircraft chasing the object
text:
Unusuall objects in the sky over Blacksburg, VA 
 
On Friday, September 27, 2019 at approximately 8:40pm in Blacksburg, Virginia, I was outside walking my dog on the trail and as usual, looking up into the sky to see what I could see. My first thoughts of the night were who exactly gets to occupy which altitudes in the sky? Because I noticed several aircraft in the air that evening, some at extremely high altitudes and others seemingly occupying various other levels of the atmosphere. 
 
 One aircraft in particular, that I presume to be of the private variety local to the Virginia Tech airport was flying in unusual patterns with a green, white and red light on it. I had taken the time to watch it carefully because it appeared to be unusual compared to the other aircraft I am accustomed to seeing in the air at night. 
 
 Considering I observe a lot of aircraft in the sky, it‚Äôs a regular occurrence here in Blacksburg, this particular aircraft was behaving in a way that made me consider the possibility some kind of driver‚Äôs education, behind the wheel class was going on? A minute or so would pass as I continued walking down the path and I looked up into the sky again to see the most amazing things. 
 
 There were three objects in the sky, one at the 11, 12 and 2 o‚Äôclock positions and they appear to be on fire. They were clustered together, seemingly moving independent of one another but the object at the 2 o‚Äôclock position moved around freely, very firefly, serpentine like and appeared to change altitudes and directions efficiently. 
 
There was a rocket booster looking affect to the objects, but they were clearly emitting some kind of flame. 
 
 Unfortunately, I did not have my camera with me but I did sprint in vein in an attempt to get one. By that point, the objects were gone. The airplane I saw moving erratically in the sky no doubt was observing this same behavior and there was an uptick in traffic in my area immediately following the event, so I would have to think it was witnessed by more than just myself on ground level.

text:
outside with my mom, flat row of lights that seemed to dance and disappear showing up a mile away or right over our head in same second 
 
Me and my mother went out on our back porch for a cigarette. While she was talking to me I could see about 7 lights in a line slowly moving into view. these lights never deviated or changed position making it seem to be 1 craft. My mom could see my face as I thought in my head "If that thing starts moving, I am OUTTA HERE" sure enough as my mom turns around slowly in horror it now starts heading our way. recorded a video and dialogue between my mom and I as well as the craft is captured. craft was a compilation of 7 small lights bundled closely together. craft almost 'waited' for my mom to turn around as well before it started its dance. it would quickly maneuver 3 different directions impossibly before going completely invisible and showing up miles or a mile from last seen area. it did this maybe 5 or 6 times IN 5 or 6 seconds. Moved so quickly even my mother kept saying Why?? lights were pink on outside edges with violet or purple for the inside! 5 lights. its movements defied conventional physics, Newtonian forces would have destroyed anything else attempting that. As scared as i was, i did not want my mom to run inside without me. I explained to my mother that this craft is the united states navy x-37 - using mass reduction drive together with piezoelectric superconducting material (ultrasonic vibrations causing noble gas to ionize) she understandably didn't know what the hell i was talking about. I explained 'Ok, its meant to refill combat planes on the field, needing those movements and maneuvers not just to get around but to evade incoming fire . craft was with us for around 5 minutes now appearing overhead and a mile away in the same second. finally in the video (video shows craft as 1 blurry purple ball) I say 'Oh i think i can hear it, sounds exactly like an airplane' because craft was completely silent the entire time, as i said that i could see a regular commercial airline start to come around from the to! ps of houses. As soon as that happened, this craft became ...e! mbarrass ed? it stopped moving crazy and put itself on a straight trajectory, accelerating instantly but not going too insanely fast it b-lined until it went below horizon. my mother wouldn't go to sleep unless she found something similar online. which she did amazingly, and only based on the movements it was doing in the video were exactly the same speed and velocity as we saw. by 4 am my mother finally went to sleep content with what she saw online and in person that night. still confused, but happy someone else had filmed it. (object did leave a trail once before disappearing, prompting my body to think the ground was moving. I stood up but only that once did it seem to bounce and leave a trail)

summary: flat topped, upside down cone, clear lights with different sized circles that expanded and contracted
stats: Occurred : 10/1/2019 22:30  (Entered as : 10/01/19 22:30) Reported: 10/12/2019 12:40:20 AM 00:40 Posted: 12/1/2019 Location: East China Sea,  Shape: Cylinder Duration: 45 min Characteristics: There were lights on the object
text:
flat topped, upside down cone, clear lights with different sized circles that expanded and contracted 
 
I was a passenger on the Ponant Le Laperouse cruise ship traveling with my family from Hong Kong to Taiwan.  My room was at the very back of the ship.  After dinner I was sitting on the deck listening to an audio book.  Sky was clear.  Stars were evident.  Some haze at water level.  It was dark.  Very little light. 
 
At about 10 pm I noticed a circular set of clear lights rotating counter clockwise slightly above the haze and seemingly close to the ship.  My first thought was it was a drone.  I kept watching for about 15 minutes.  Periodically, It would rapidly move vertically--up and down.  I went inside our room and got my husband who agreed it was something odd.  I then used a set of binoculars, and easily found the the flat topped upside down cone shaped thing.  It had circles on the side that expanded and contracted, all in clear lights.  Circles were of different sizes and looked liked watching a cell under a microscope.  Moving, contracting and expanding circles.  I watched this for nearly 30 minutes. 
 
I have no explanation why I didn't notify the bridge or take a photo.  I did think, that I would ask the ship the next day and I assumed they would have seen it from the bridge--- as it was very clearly there.  I assumed they had cameras that would record it.  I did not attempt to take a photo.  Regrettably I do not know why.  I was actually rather mesmerized by this object.  After about 45 minutes, it disappeared. 
 
The following morning I asked the ship's captain if they had seen it.  He seemed to know nothing about it, but did seem interested in my account.  He said the ship's drone was not flying and they did not have cameras that film off the back of the ship.  The bridge faces forward which explains why they did not see behind the ship. 
 
I have looked around online to see if I can see a drawing or photo of what I saw, but have seen nothing like it.  So thought I would simply report it.

summary: Three bright white lights in a perfect triangle pattern that then disappeared to reappear as a blue streak moving at great speed.
stats: Occurred : 10/2/2019 01:30  (Entered as : 10/02/19 01:30) Reported: 10/18/2019 1:30:11 PM 13:30 Posted: 12/1/2019 Location: Crestline, KS Shape: Triangle Duration: 30 Seconds Characteristics: There were lights on the object, The object left a trail, The object changed color
text:
Three bright white lights in a perfect triangle pattern that then disappeared to reappear as a blue streak moving at great speed. 
 
I work as an airport firefighter.  My shift starts at 2:00am.  Since, I make this drive in the dark everyday, I'm very familiar with the normal towers, FAA obstruction beacons and such.  On my drive in, near the small town of Crestline, KS.  I looked North and noticed three very bright white lights in a perfect triangle pattern.  They appeared to be hovering in place, possibly as low as 100-200 feet off the ground, but at night it's hard to judge that.  Confused, as I knew there wasn't anything in that area cell-tower wise, my first thought was a possible military helicopter formation with their forward facing landing lights on.  Again, since I work in aviation on the graveyard shift, I'm used to seeing aircraft lighting.  However, these lights didn't have any of the other mandated FAA aircraft lighting.  For example, there were no red beacons, no green and red directional lighting, none of it.  Just three, perfectly still, perfectly symmetrical bright white! lights.  Over the next 15-30 seconds, I had to keep looking back at the road since I was driving 65mph.  Each time I looked away, one of the lights would disappear.  First there was three, then I looked back and there were only two, then one.  Until they were all gone.  Still confused as to what I had seen I was simply looking in the general direction of the now dark space the lights previously occupied, and suddenly I saw a bright blue flash, followed by something streaking to the west as fast as I've ever seen anything move in my life. Huge Triangle shaped objects in formation over Port Orchard, WA.

On a clear evening, Big Dipper was very clear, my Dad and I were si
stats: Occurred : 10/2/2019 22:21  (Entered as : 10/02/2019 22:21) Reported: 11/1/2019 7:28:17 PM 19:28 Posted: 12/1/2019 Location: Port Orchard, WA Shape: Triangle Duration: 2-3 seconds
text:
Huge Triangle shaped objects in formation over Port Orchard, WA. 
 
On a clear evening, Big Dipper was very clear, my Dad and I were sitting around a campfire. He was sitting next to me and said ‚Äúlook‚Äù in a surprised and alarmed voice.  I was looking down but looked up and saw a very huge formation of triangles.   At first it resembled a flock of geese but immediately new that was wrong. It resemble a flock of geese because of it‚Äôs  ‚ÄòV‚Äô formation and the distance between the triangles was similar to the distance between geese. 
 
The size was amazing.  If I extend my arm and extend my hand it nearly took up my entire hand.  There were 5 or 6 triangles on the left part of the ‚ÄòV‚Äô and 5 or 6 on the other right hand part.  Over to the right was another ‚ÄòV‚Äô shape but further away or at a different angle.  We only saw this object for 2-3 seconds.  It was flying from east to west,  almost directly over our heads..  Each triangle was the same shape and size.  The size of each one is difficult to determine.  I drive to Seattle Tacoma International airport frequently and when I see an airplane in the pattern I put my hand up in front of me to try to gauge the size in comparison.  All the aircraft around Sea Tac appear to be small compared to these triangles.  Both my Dad and I seemed to think the object was very high in the sky.  My estimate is that each triangle was the size of 2-4 large aircraft nose to tail. 
 
Each triangle was perpendicular to the earth.  The entire formation moved as one and traveled sideways.  Each triangle appeared to be separate. There was nothing visible that connected them. There was no apparent indication of movement.  There was no sound.  It seemed to move with great speed.  From the time we first spotted it to when it left our field of vision was 3 seconds top.  We could see it getting smaller as it flew towards the Olympic Mountains. We think it flew out of our sight. If so the speed would be incredible.  We regularly see jets flying towards the north end of the mountains on their way to Asia.  We see these aircraft for more than a minute.  Port Orchard is approximately 30 miles from Sea Tac. 
 
There were no lights we associate with aviation. The only light was a white-yellowish glow coming from each triangle.  The glow was contained to the middle in a slight oval shape. Some of the light spilled over to reveal straight edges of the triangle. Each of the triangles had the same color and light amount.

text:
Early in the morning of October 4th 2019 around 4am I was letting my dogs out in the backyard.  Per usual I was looking up at the sky when I saw a large object seemingly hovering around in the same spot.  There was a weird light zipping around the object that I was able to get on video. 
 
When looking up at the sky there was an object that seemed quite large hovering in a small area. There were several lights around the bottom of the object which is how I was able to see it slightly moving in sort of a circle.  I assumed, at first, that it was a plane, but as I stood there it didn't seem to be really going anywhere.  It seemed to be very high up above the clouds, though it still seemed quite large. 
 
I decided to try to film what was going on with my phone. It couldn't quite pick up the large object even zoomed in as far as it would go.  It did, though, pick up a strange white light that seemed to just be zipping around the sky around the larger object.  This object moved very quickly in a random pattern back and forth around the larger object.  It seemed to almost disappear for a super brief period and then it would reappear on the other side of the larger object in the blink of an eye. 
 
As I said, I did get it on video and have watched it several times and even had my husband and sister watch it and we cannot figure out what could be moving around in such a way.  I don't want to just jump to UFO, but I cannot come up with any other explanation. If there was something that was going on at this time of morning in the sky I haven't been able to find it when googling for possible answers.

summary: Saw a bright V formation that looked like birds in the dark night sky, it flew over faster than any bird formation I have ever seen.
stats: Occurred : 10/5/2019 02:19  (Entered as : 10/5/2019 2:19) Reported: 10/5/2019 12:46:33 PM 12:46 Posted: 12/1/2019 Location: Destin, FL Shape: Disk Duration: ~1-2 minutes Characteristics: There were lights on the object
text:
Saw a bright V formation that looked like birds in the dark night sky, it flew over faster than any bird formation I have ever seen. 
 
I often see comets or shooting stars as I sit on a bench on my front porch. Sometimes they are like a thin white streak through the night sky. Sometimes they are closer to earth and are a bright beautiful yellow. I enjoy seeing these, so I will often try to catch them. Last night at 2:19 or so I was sitting and I noticed something above in my peripheral.  I looked up and it is a perfect v flying against the night sky.  Glowing, and I am immediately out of my seat, rationalizing it to myself.  Those are birds. It looks almost like the V birds make but somehow perfect and they are moving totally unlike birds. Nothing is staggered, it's almost like it's coasting.  The light had seemed extremely bright when it was basically over top of me, but once it started to move rapidly away, it began to get slightly dimmer, but I could still easily see it against the night sky. In no time at all the V is getting longer and longer in the distance.  The formation is heading towar! ds town so I can see the shape against the slightly lit up backdrop above the trees and I swear before it dipped below I could see the outline of a ship.  It seemed wide like a saucer but thicker height wise then what I generally think of a saucer. 
 
 I have lived here for more than a year.  It is a tourist town on the coast and there is a military base very nearby.  The Eglin Air Force Base. Basically this town is tourists and military members. I have never had an encounter like this before. I was on the phone with a friend of mine just screaming, "What is that? That is not normal." Because, it wasn't. Airplanes fly over my all the time.  I am used to the roar at all hours of the night. I have watched from the beach as the air force practiced flying their jets in formation, and my daughter cried because it was literally too loud for her.  I know what ships sound and look like in the sky, but whatever I saw last night was totally silent. No hum to the air. No roar as it passed by.  I was terrified and giddy all at the same time.  I almost started to cry, because in the midst of this thing I did not understand I realized it was sort of a gift.  I am writing this in the hopes that you maybe get something from around this! area last night, that someone else saw something and I am not crazy.  Even if no one else did see though, I never thought I would get to see something like it.  It was a singular experience that was difficult to describe. I hope it helps!

summary: SOLID OBJECT EMITTING A CLOUD AROUND IT
stats: Occurred : 10/5/2019 03:55  (Entered as : 10/5/19 03:55) Reported: 10/18/2019 7:50:49 PM 19:50 Posted: 12/1/2019 Location: Warrenton, MO Shape: Chevron Duration: 15 seconds
text:
SOLID OBJECT EMITTING A CLOUD AROUND IT 
 
It was a clear night and not a cloud in the sky north and northwest of us. To the South the sky was cloudy due to rain. As I was enjoying the stars, I noticed something traveling at the tree line that appeared to be a huge oblong shaped cloud from a distance. It was traveling about 30 miles per hour and as it reached the front of my house, I looked closer and noticed it was a solid object emitting smoke all over it as if it were trying to appear to be a cloud. The entire time not once did this object make not one noise; in fact, it was very quiet and still when this flew by. 
 
I then said to my husband ‚Äúwhat is that?!‚Äù, he turned around and watched it through the tree, when suddenly it made a hard left and we noticed a wing; as it floated east, I quickly went inside frightened as I have never seen this before. My husband watched it disappear through a tree line behind our house and got a clearer view as it floated away, he claims it was chevron shaped. It had zero lights on it, and was like a dark charcoal gray inside of the cloud appearance. 
 
I really wish I would have had my phone to take a video, but this thing flew by so quick I did not have time to get my phone. We both lost sleep over this that night and spent hours researching what we saw.

summary: 3 Objects, triangle formation, irregular, rapidly blinking pattern of red lights over Milpitas California.
stats: Occurred : 10/7/2019 17:40  (Entered as : 10/07/19 17:40) Reported: 10/8/2019 8:59:46 PM 20:59 Posted: 12/1/2019 Location: Milpitas, CA Shape: Formation Duration: 5 minutes Characteristics: There were lights on the object, There were aircraft in the vicinity or aircraft chasing the object
text:
3 Objects, triangle formation, irregular, rapidly blinking pattern of red lights over Milpitas California. 
 
At approximately 9:40 pm, I heard the distinctive sound of fighter jets passing overhead. 
 
We hear that maybe once a month or so & I often run out back to watch what seem to be F18s or F15s fly by usually n pairs, usually heading roughly south. we live very near Moffett field as well as the San Jose Airport & a small airport for private planes I believe is called "Reid‚ÄìHillview" for private planes.  The sky is always full of planes, big & small, commercial & military. Google & NASA both have a presence at Moffett. 
 
On this occasion is was dark, night time, a not entirely black sky, very polluted with with lights was full of planes as always. 2 Fighters were heading south at a moderate altitude (probably several thousand feet) they had several sets of lights on. In an unusual twist only a few minutes later a second set was heard. I went out back again and watch 2 more fighters streak loudly southward. 
 
Both times I called my 8 year old son out to see, the second time I called out the whole family. My wife & daughter, not terribly interested took a long time to come out by which time my son & I had been watching a bizarre, triangle formation of red & only red lights crossing the the entire sky from the Santa Cruz mountains, eventually passing over the TV & radio towers on the peak of the east hills. 
 
It took about 2-3 minutes for the formation of objects to cross the entire sky & disappear from view, into the distance. The objects held a distant but incredibly accurate triangle formation. The red lights were not "blinking" in a regular pattern, they were alternating in an ever-changing coordinated, often very rapid sequence like no aircraft or group of aircraft that I, personally have ever seen.  There was no discernible repetition or pattern to the blinking.  It seemed coordinated & deliberate almost like Morse Code or music. 
 
As the objects passed over the nearby foothills they took a surprisingly long time to disappear into the distance.  To me this was an indication that they were higher & larger than they had initially appeared.  There was no particular sound that seemed associated with these particular objects.  Usually we can associate the many sounds coming from the crowded sky with the objects responsible.  The fighters for example are far louder than anything else ever is. 
 
There were a hand full of other odd characters in the sky that night.  Presumably & seemingly conventional aircraft with somewhat odd light patterns, always-on bright white lights, more & brighter lights than the usual commercial or private aircraft seeming to circle around the entirety of the silicon valley for most of an hour before/after the strange triangle passed overhead. 
 
My son and I watched this formation from one horizon to the other.  My wife & daughter saw the second half. I didn't go for my camera because I didn't want to miss anything.  Most likely this was a formation of drones or stealth fighters.  The lights were weird to the point that they must have been made deliberately weird.  I wish I had footage so I could try to figure out which symphony or what Morse code message some Goole nerd had probably programmed into the light pattern just to be a smart ass . 
 
What ever it was I didn't particularly like it, less for it's weirdness & more for it's condescension.

summary: 7 People on a pontoon witnessed a cylinder object about 3/4 mile West of Anclote Key Preserve State Park in the Gulf of Mexico
stats: Occurred : 10/7/2019 21:35  (Entered as : 10/07/19 21:35) Reported: 10/7/2019 9:28:54 AM 09:28 Posted: 12/1/2019 Location: Anclote Key State Park, FL Shape: Cylinder Duration: 4 minutes
text:
7 People on a pontoon witnessed a cylinder object about 3/4 mile West of Anclote Key Preserve State Park in the Gulf of Mexico 
 
We were on my pontoon boat - we had spent most of the afternoon on Anclote Key Preserve State Park and the Sandbars that are just to the North of the park.  There were 7 of us on the boat.  We left the sandbars and headed out about 7 miles as the sun was setting, towards a reef sight and known fish haven.  Because of the storms that had passed through earlier, the water was rough, with 3-foot seas, we decided to make a turn South and then head back just after the sun had set.  We were pulling a jet ski so we could only move at around 4-5 mph in fear of snapping the tow line.  As we were approaching the pass between the Anclote Key Preserve and the sandbars, two of the people on the front of the boat started talking about seeing what they thought was a bag or a balloon sitting on the water up ahead and to the right of the boat.  We had no lights, other than standard navigational lights on at the time, however, because of the moisture in the air, the city lights were causing the water to have enough light reflected on it to see ahead in the water.  As we approached the object, the 4 guests on the front of the boat were trying to figure out what it was, going back and forth as to whether it was a big plastic bag, a balloon or maybe even a big bird of some sort.  However, as we got closer is was apparent that the object was bigger than everyone though, probably around 4-5 feet across, cylinder in shape and maybe 4 to 5 feet tall.  As we came to with 100 feet or so of the object, it lifted quickly into the air straight up and hovered at around 8 to 10 feet off the water.  It was a dull color, and you could tell it was solid but had no shininess to it at all.  Everyone on the boat sat in silence and disbelief as we passed by the object to the right of the boat as it just sat there. No sound, no lights - nothing.  Once passed, I turned to everyone and asked, 'Did you all just see that?' and everyone was still looking trying to see it.  I turned! on my flood/spot lights, and turned the boat around because w! e all st ill thought it was something that may have been attached to the water and floating, but none of us seen any sort of cable or string attaching it to anything.  After turning around, and making a couple of passes in the shape of a figure 8, we did not see the object again.  We discussed the object all the way back in to the dock and we do not know what it was that we say.  We all were in agreement that it was NOT as balloon, bag or bird of anny kind.  We all believe it was a solid object, or what appeared to be very solid.

text:
10/07/19  22:15  San Jose, Calif.  Triangle  3 minutes  I saw 3 red small lights in a fixed triangular formation traveling very slow. 
 
I was visiting McDonald's restaurant last night on Blossom Hill Rd. and Kooser Ave. while sitting in my car in the parking lot with the window open I started hearing a noise that sounded like someone dragging a big bag of rocks across the sidewalk very slowly. as I exited my vehicle I looked up above my head into the night sky.  I saw 3 distinct small red lights in triangular formation that were blinking together but not always consistent.  This area above my head in the sky always has heavy commercial airline traffic. I was walking back to my apartment counting planes in the sky when I noticed a bright orange and yellowish light coming over the top of the building.  At first I thought it was so low I could throw a baseball and hit it and it must be a drone but as it passed overhead I could tell it was big and solid and cylindrical like a cigar.  I noted that I could hear other planes but this made no sound even though it was so much closer.  I remember thinking to myself multiple times ‚Äútake a picture‚Äù but I was so intrigued I just watched it.  As it moved further into the distance it appeared to bend backwards vertically, like a bow, and meandered left then right.  I went inside and told my girlfriend about it.  I decided to go back out and see if I could still see it.  It had come from the south and moved north.  Now I saw it, or something very much like it, coming from the southeast - if it was the same object it appeared to be circling the area.  I collected my wits and took a! picture with my iPhone. This all occurred within a timeframe of roughly 40 minutes. 
 
The object did not leave a trail behind it and made no sound.  I do not believe it was a plane or helicopter or drone.  I am emailing the photograph I took.

summary: Red-orange lights over Myrtle Beach
stats: Occurred : 10/8/2019 23:00  (Entered as : 10/08/19 23:00) Reported: 10/17/2019 8:54:21 AM 08:54 Posted: 12/1/2019 Location: Myrtle Beach, SC Shape: Sphere Duration: 4 or 5 min Characteristics: There was an aura or haze around the object, The object emitted other objects
text:
Red-orange lights over Myrtle Beach 
 
I was at Myrtle Beach with my elderly mother and her two friends for the week. It was a Tuesday night on Oct. 8. The ladies were already in bed for the night and I was out on a 3rd floor hotel balcony overlooking the beach boardwalk. I was drinking bourbon at the time.  It was around 23:00 and as I looks northward up the beach, I noticed Orangish Red lights in the air moving south following the beach. Weather was very cloudy and these lights were below the clouds. There was southward wind around 10 mph. as we were having poor weather last few days. 
 
 I first glance I thought all the tourist helicopters were flying down the beach with a landing or spotlight on. I though it was cool, an evening air show of sorts. But then the several lights started dropping other reddish orange lights from the bottom. Just like them but smaller. These lights descended a bit and disappeared. First thought was roman candles or flares. 
 
 I then noticed there was no sound coming from the objects. The tourist helicopters were loud, and I should be hearing them, but I wasn‚Äôt. As they drew closer. Still dropping their lights. I noticed there was no red or green wing tip lights. Just the reddish glow of the objects themselves. But still no engine noise. 
 
 As first one was in front of the hotel and myself, I noticed no white blinking tail light either. Just a spherical light at about a 45-degree angle, below the clouds.  And still no noise. It was at this time I woke my mother to look and see if she was seeing what I was seeing. She started watching the event mid-way through and also wondered what they were and also noticed no sound from them. The objects were still continuing to drop other lights. This entire time. My thinking if these were flares, they would illuminate the ground or water, but didn‚Äôt. they just dropped and dissipated. They were dropping light so frequently, there would be three small lights under the main. As the forth light would drop the first would dissipate. 
 
After 8 or 10 moved by the last one in the formation which unlike the others, was not dropping lights came by, and as they moved south disappeared into the low clouds. The objects in front were still dropping lights as I could no longer see them but the dropped lights still appeared as they fell below the clouds. This entire event lasted 4 or 5 min. 
 
 I still have no clue what I saw. I have considered drones, but cannot explain the dropping of the lights. I have considered candle balloons as they were moving south with a southern wind direction with pieces of the burning materials falling off. But the straight-line formation along with the regularity of the dropping lights discounts that to me. 
 
I frequent airshows. I am a fan of military aviation, and I can identify aircraft as I see them fly over. Not being able to explain this is irritating to me. I do not believe in UFOs. I still don‚Äôt. However, there is video footage online that is very similar to what I saw. And I finally realized I had a cell phone to record this and I did video the last sphere as it went by. But as I said. It was not dropping lights like the others so I have no proof of that activity. 
 
 If I was to describe this in UFO terms. Foo Fighter seems to match.

summary: I was driving along Dyer Lake Road, approaching McHenry street, on my way to work. It was dark still, the sun was about 10 minutes from
stats: Occurred : 10/9/2019 05:45  (Entered as : 10/9/2019 05:45) Reported: 10/9/2019 2:24:55 PM 14:24 Posted: 12/1/2019 Location: Bohners Lake, WI Shape: Cone Duration: 4 seconds Characteristics: There were lights on the object
text:
I was driving along Dyer Lake Road, approaching McHenry street, on my way to work.  It was dark still, the sun was about 10 minutes from lighting up the sky.  But the sky was crystal clear deep blue/black and there wasn't much tree cover from the sides.  I noticed to my upper left field of view a sudden bright light and that it's moving fast. 
 
I thought it was a shooting star (my thought as it entered my peripheral vision) so I got excited and looked at it and IMMEDIATELY could tell that it wasn't a shooting star.  It had hard edges to it and there were giant red circular lights on the back of it, with some smaller? (really ambiguous) white light near the red.  It was a hexigonal cone shape, with a flattened bottom. 
 
It traveled around the speed of a shooting star, which is what made me think what I did at first. It went very quickly from my left field of view to my right and then made a VERY hard and sudden left turn and as soon as it completed the turn, it disappeared.  There was a very very VERY unnoticable white blink when it disappeared. Very subtle. 
 
So the best way I can describe its flight path was ‚úì (but flipped around, and it was more horizontal/parallel to the ground). 
 
There was no sound, no sonic booms, no loud engine sounds.  It was relatively low to the ground as well, no higher than a mid-alttitude plane.  If I had to guess, maybe 3,000-4,000 feet off the ground. 
 
All happened I'm about 3-4 seconds and I didn't take my eyes off of it until it vanished, and even still I kept looking up at the sky.  I was driving slowly along a relatively straight road so with no body around.  So my focus was on the sky for a good couple minutes after that.  
 
Didn't see anything else though.

summary: I saw a very, very bright light in the eastern sky above/behind mountain range. It lasted only seconds-it appeared then disappeared.
stats: Occurred : 10/9/2019 06:45  (Entered as : 10/9/2019 6:45) Reported: 10/9/2019 9:58:07 AM 09:58 Posted: 12/1/2019 Location: Albuquerque, NM Shape: Light Duration: Seconds Characteristics: There were lights on the object, There were aircraft in the vicinity or aircraft chasing the object
text:
I saw a very, very bright light in the eastern sky above/behind mountain range. It lasted only seconds-it appeared then disappeared. 
 
October 9, 2019  This morning I was driving to an appointment I had at the VA Hospital in Albuquerque, NM.  My wife and I moved to Albuquerque late last year.  I saw a stationary, very, very bright white light above the Sandia Mountain range at approximately 6:45AM.  It was difficult to look directly at the light.  When I saw the light I was traveling east on the Paseo del Norte (an east west four lane highway).  The light lasted just a few seconds before it "winked" out.  I didn't see a tail that one would see if it were a meteor.  I can't say if the light was above the mountain range or east of the range.  At whatever distance it was at it appeared to be the size of a pin head.  I don't know if it was a UFO.   
 
Currently, Albuquerque is celebrating the annual Balloon Fiesta.  The fiesta started last weekend and ends this weekend.  There were balloons in the sky but they were all above the Balloon Park or spread out to the north.  It was no more than 5-15 minutes after the light went out that I saw a helicopter flying south towards the general location of the light.  The helicopter may have turned east, but the distance was too far for me to be sure if it went east or turned west.  By then I was merging onto Interstate 25 going south to the VA hospital.  One thought that occurred to me at the time was that the light I observed was a star becoming a super nova.  A second thought was that it may have been an airplane coming in to land at the Albuquerque airport.  I scratched that idea by the way the light disappeared and its high intensity.  By the way, there were no stars to be seen in this part of the sky as the sun was up on the other side of the mountain range.  I'm sure other people driving east would have seen the same light.  There were hundreds of cars on the road heading to work or the balloon park.

summary: Erratic bright light hovers, moves, then vanishes.
stats: Occurred : 10/9/2019 06:55  (Entered as : 10/09/2019 06:55) Reported: 10/9/2019 3:04:49 PM 15:04 Posted: 12/1/2019 Location: Greenville, PA Shape: Light Duration: 1 minute Characteristics: The object changed color, There were aircraft in the vicinity or aircraft chasing the object
text:
Erratic bright light hovers, moves, then vanishes. 
 
I arrived at my construction job site at around 06:45. I dropped off my tools and opened the garage doors to get ready for the day. Since I had a few moments, I stepped outside to feel the morning air, I noticed a fairly bright "Star" to the West of the warehouse where I stood. 
 
The "Star" was larger than the average star on this early morning, it had a reddish orange hue, and flickered every so slightly. I assumed that it was Mars, just peeking out over the rooftops. 
 
I downloaded the Skymaps app last week, so I open the app expecting the object to be Mars. However, nothing celestial was in that vicinity, especially not something that bright. 
 
My second logical assumption was that it was an aircraft, or perhaps a satellite; however unusual, since the light was as bright as Mars typically is. I watched the object and was able to realize that it was in fact moving. However, it was behaving erratically. Up up up, to the right, wobble, up up up, to the right, wobble; ever so slightly. 
 
Perhaps it was a helicopter with a spotlight?  Then my periphery, an easily identifiable airplane was also crossing the sky.  Two blinking lights, white and red. Traveling toward the general area that the mysterious object occupied. 
 
I went back to watching the strange light, only for a few seconds more; in an instant it vanished.  As the light suddenly cut out, in the exact same spot; a barely visible red light zipped to the right, much more horizontal than vertical.  The speed in which this tiny red light moved was frightening at first glance, it reminded me of how one sees a meteorite zipping across the atmosphere before burning out. It moved so quickly and was so faint that I lost sight of it. 
 
Its hard to estimate the exact distance and direction of the object, but if I was to get as close as I could;  From the horizon it was approximately 20 degrees vertical.  On a 360 Degree compass, it was approximately 15 degrees clockwise of due West.  I can't give an accurate estimation of distance seeing as it was only a light, but if I was to guess based on gut feeling,  I would bet about 15 to 20 miles or so as the bird flies.

text:
Glittering cylindrical object over East Dayton. 
 
I went out on our back patio at approx 10:00 pm on 10/9/19 to smoke.  As I was sitting there, I noticed a bright light in the NE sky.  I started watching it because of how bright it was and because the lights weren't horizontal in the sky but vertical. 
 
Over the course of the next 45 minutes, I watched this object which never deviated more than a couple of degrees from its position.  It seemed to be a cylindrical object with lights that made it look like it was glittering.  The lights would change from red to green to blue and, whenever I would see an obvious airplane in the sky near it, the lights would change to a bright white.  Once the aircraft was beyond a certain range, it would go back to the r/g/b rotation.  After approx 30 minutes, the shape of the craft changed to a tiny pinpoint of light which made me think that it had suddenly taken off but, to my surprise, after about 20 seconds it reappeared the same as it had been before.  This happened several times over the next 10 minutes.  I finally had to go inside so don't know how long this object was in the sky.  Did not take any photos as all I had was my cell phone and I knew with it being night and the distance to the object, it would pretty much be useless to try to capture what I was seeing.

summary: A large black pencil shaped object sped by the width of the moon  as observed through my telescope at 23:30 hrs on 10/09/19.
stats: Occurred : 10/9/2019 23:30  (Entered as : 10/09/19 23:30) Reported: 10/9/2019 11:09:53 PM 23:09 Posted: 12/1/2019 Location: Las Cruces, NM Shape: Cigar Duration: 1 second or less
text:
A large black pencil shaped object sped by the width of the moon  as observed through my telescope at 23:30 hrs on 10/09/19. 
 
I was looking at the moon about 23:30 hours on October, 09, 2019 when I observed a large black shape quickly shoot past from my left to right through the lens. I was using a Twinstar F500mm scope with a 6 in mirror and a 25mm lens with a barlow attached.  The moon almost filled my whole view when all of a sudden and without any lights I could see and no noise, a black pencil shaped object swooped across the screen from left to right. Through my lens it appeared to be 1/16 of an inch thick and about 1 inch long. It happened so fast, very fast. It was alone that I could see and appeared to be slightly thicker toward the tail end. There was no noise. I continued to follow the moon for another 15 minutes with no other sightings.  It was not a bird, airplane, or any other object known to me. summary: At 20:30 we (me and my wife) went for the smoke break (we're not smoking in house 'cause of kids). Right after lighting up
stats: Occurred : 10/10/2019 20:30  (Entered as : 10/10/2019 20:30) Reported: 10/10/2019 8:05:38 PM 20:05 Posted: 12/1/2019 Location: Waltham, MA Shape: Unknown Duration: 30 minutes Characteristics: There were lights on the object
text:
At 20:30 we (me and my wife) went for the "smoke break" (we're not smoking in house 'cause of kids). Right after lighting up 
 
At 20:30 we (me and my wife) went for the "smoke break" (we're not smoking in house 'cause of kids).  Right after lighting up my cigarette, I found a light in the night sky, over Prospect Hill, and not very high.  Light was strange 'cause it doesn't looks like plane or helicopter.  I called out my wife, and we started watching that light.  After few minutes, I grabbed binocular (x30) and tried to watch object via optics, but it wasn't helpful, object still looks like a bright light.  After few minutes we noticed a second light, and little bit later the third.  These lights are slowly floated/moved in the sky. 
 
Fortunately, I do have a telescope, cheap one (truly :), this model  
 
https://www.aliexpress.com/item/32968885736.html?spm=a2g0s.9042311.0.0.f2f34c4dRnKHpZ  
 
However this telescope has good aperture (76 mm).  After few tries I captured one of slowly moving objects by eyepiece (it wasn't easy 'cause of cheap telescope design, and because objects was relatively low).  But it's really hard or even impossible to estimate a real distance to objects, and real altitude. 
 
By the way, in the telescope I was able to see object a little bit close.  It looks like it has bright white-yellow light in front (like a lamp or cockpit window or I don't know...), and two small flashing lights on the sides.  These lights was mounted on airship-like dark body (but I'm unsure about shape and size).  I thought it's some kind of drone or quadcopter, but more it looks like mini-airship with mounted lights. 
 
All of these objects drifted slowly (but very slowly) or hung in the night sky; after 10 or 15 minutes one object started moving little bit faster and disappeared from sight soon (unfortunately, trees on our backyard are blocking view). Another object appeared after 2 or 3 minutes, and it came not from the ground (like a quadcopter, for example) but afar from the south. 
 
Finally, all these objects were darkened and disappeared at about 21:00-21:10. But another similar object was appeared just before I called you, at 21:50 (I went smoke, saw the object - but it was dimmer than before, and decided to call). Periodically I checked sky in that direction but haven't seen anything else. 
 
I do not know what it was:  military or private company night tests of drones/airships (flashing lights on the side looks like human made - spaceships/probes don't need small flashing lights at all), but something wasn't right. Who will allow that kind of tests in the highly populated area? Kids are playing or flash-mobbing? According to flight time and luminous intensity, it's not a regular retail quadcopters with LED flashlight attached. 
 
I don't know.

text:
Seattle World's Fair- June, 1962 
 
Sorry about the date info. I wanted to file this report and couldn't figure out how to get the date in correctly. 
 
I was 10 years old and at the base of Space Needle with my father. We looked up and saw approximately six hovering discs. Heat was coming off of them. They moved in various configurations and heights. They would disappear and reappear. They would scramble, then align and hover. The final move was to ascend into the sky at high rate of speed and vanish. 
In my adult years, (around 50 years old) my father and I discussed this citing. We both reconfirmed what we saw and our recollections were consistent. There was NO DOUBT about what we saw. 
 
I recently scoured local archives to see if anyone had reported a similar citing. No reports found. 
 
Also recently, there was an article in the Seattle Times about UFO's and about your agency. That is why I am writing. I am 70 years old, of sound mind. This IS a true and honest account. I would be curious to know if anyone else reported this. Please feel free to contact me...

stats: Occurred : 12/5/1962  Reported: 8/23/2007 15:08 Posted: 12/22/2022 Location: Pacific Ocean (in flight),  Shape:
text:
The second sighting I would like to mention was related by my flight examiner navigator, then a Captain, later a Major, named Jordan W. Grant.  We called him "Pappy Grant" and he was probably in his forties at the time. 
 
On December 5, 1962, I was given a line check from Pappy, again to Rhein Main. 
 
During our two-day crew rest in Germany, we had several meals together and at one of them, Pappy related the following story. 
 
It was during a mission in over the Pacific and Pappy was navigating.  It was daylight and Pappy had the LORAN set on as well as the radar (which was always on when it was working correctly).  Suddenly the display on the LORAN scope and the display on the radar scope shrunk, leaving only a dot in the middle of each scope.  The compasses began to gyrate wildly. 
 
Pappy stuck his head into the cockpit and found the pilots gibbering incoherently and looking fearfully back as best they could from their side windows.  Pappy asked what had happened.  Finally, they calmed down enough to tell him.  One told him that a flaming red ball had just nearly hit them head-on and that he was afraid that it might return.  The second said the same thing but claimed that there were four balls instead of just one.  The ball or balls had been at the same altitude as the airplane and flying straight and level. 
 
Eventually, the radar, the LORAN set, and the compasses returned to normal. 
 
Chances are Pappy is no longer alive.  He had a master's degree in marine biology and worked on his own blueberry farm with his wife between missions.  He would eat two large steaks whenever he could and enjoyed good food perhaps more than he should have.  If you have any suggestions on how to find either John or Pappy, please let me know.  A search on line might help.  Pappy was more than just a flight examiner with a higher rank than most of us.  He was a valuable friend to us all. 
 
 
((NUFORC Note:  Witness elects to remain totally anonymous;  provides no contact information.  PD))

summary: In pitch dark, bright light came out of rain clouds, hovered above trees, then abruptly turned; left horizontally.
stats: Occurred : 8/4/1971 20:30  (Entered as : 08/04/1971 8:30 PM) Reported: 10/18/2022 3:23:16 PM 15:23 Posted: 12/22/2022 Location: Lesterville, MO Shape: Light Duration: 3 minutes Characteristics: There were lights on the object
text:
In pitch dark, bright light came out of rain clouds, hovered above trees, then abruptly turned; left horizontally. 
 
When I was 12, my father and brother and I were driving back from Pilot Knob, where some unusual lights had been spotted. We saw none. Back then there was no development in the forest between Lesterville and the campground, only unmarked forest service roads that we took every summer. A rain storm had moved in and we were driving in pitch black. An extremely bright light appeared in the dark above the trees nearby. We stopped, turned off the car and headlights, and watched. It hovered for several minutes, then moved horizontally and disappeared into the dark. The light was bright enough that we couldn't see what it was attached to, but we'd never seen anything move that way in the sky.

summary: Three disk like objects over Camels Hump in Huntington Vermont in summer of 1972
stats: Occurred : 7/12/1972 12:00  (Entered as : 07/12/1972 12:00 PM) Reported: 8/17/2022 9:59:22 AM 09:59 Posted: 12/22/2022 Location: Huntington, VT Shape: Disk Duration: 2-4 minutes Characteristics: There was an aura or haze around the object, The object made a sound, There were electrical or magnetic effects
text:
Three disk like objects over Camels Hump in Huntington Vermont in summer of 1972 
 
August 16th, 2022 
I experienced a UFO sighting when I was a little girl in Vermont. Why did I wait until now to tell my 
story? I‚Äôm 62 and felt if I didn‚Äôt do this now, I might not ever write about it! I grew-up on a dairy farm in 
the valley of the Green Mountains in Vermont with my 8 brothers and 2 sisters. I was the youngest of 
the 3 girls still living at home. My parents and 4-5 boys were still working on the farm. 
This happened on July 12, 1972. I was 12 years old and playing with one of my older brothers 
in our hand-made sand box. We would spend hours and hours upon hours running our old, metal Tonka 
trucks and cars on the hilly tracks. I remember the day and date because I knew if I did, I‚Äôd remember it 
in the years to come. 
It was a hot, clear & sunny day around lunch time. I remember the sun being high above me in the sky. 
My mother was preparing lunch in our old, post and beam farmhouse kitchen. I could hear my mom 
talking with my 18-year-old brother thru the front door. On hot days and with no AC in Vermont, 
we always kept the door open to catch any breeze. This brother had the habit of straddling his 
chair while talking to whoever was in the kitchen. 
On this day my dad and my other brothers were finishing up their chores and taking a break from haying 
in the fields. We had a farm bell on our house, so whenever she needed them, she would ring it. 
On this strange day my brother and I were outside playing in the sand box. He had just had ear 
surgery and had a white turban-like bandage wrapped around his head. My mother had sent him out to 
get some sunshine and play with me because he had been in bed all morning. I recall he still had on his 
pajamas. I was quietly playing with my truck and talking with him when I felt a strange feeling on my 
neck and upper back. My hair was tied back in a ponytail to keep it our of the way on the farm. It was a 
strange, almost electrical vibrating feeling. Starting at my neck, traveling down my back. There was this 
weird, humming sound all around me. Almost a buzzing sound, like a swarm of bees. My dad always 
told me it was hard or nearly impossible to sneak up behind be because I‚Äôd sense someone was there. I 
still feel this feeling today if someone is behind me. 
I looked up over my right my shoulder and saw three-saucer like objects hovering over Camels Hump. 
We lived just at the foothills of the green mountain forest in Huntington, Vermont. The lower trees were 
growing taller, but you could still see the upper most, rocky top. As I watched them, I had the feeling like 
they were watching us and wondering what we were doing? They were dark grey and metallic. I can 
only describe them as two saucer plates put together. They were in a triangular pattern with one on top 
and two side-by-side just below the top one. All three looked like they were hovering and spinning 
about 500-1,000 ft above the rocky top. I was thinking the sound I heard might have been from the 
spinning. It looked like there were windows along the edges. I couldn‚Äôt look away as I was watching 
them. I didn‚Äôt realize I was pointing and screaming. I wasn‚Äôt scared, just wanted someone else to see this 
other than me. The brother who I was playing with had limited hearing because of his surgery, but told me later he had seen a flash in the sky 
when he realized I was upset and where I was pointing to. 
My brother, by the front door, heard my screaming and turned his chair to come out on the front porch. I feel when 
he moved to see what was happening, his movement made the three disks darted up and leave in a 
flash! They went up and took a sharp left and was gone? It happened so quickly! It couldn‚Äôt have been more than a few seconds when I first saw them. It felt like they were 
observing my brother and I. He said he saw something but couldn‚Äôt quite make it out except that 
something caught his eye and went behind the mountain and out of sight. I wasn‚Äôt the type of sister to make things up. 
Seeing me so upset, made my family believe I was telling the truth! I just wish I wasn‚Äôt the only one to see them clearly. 
It‚Äôs been over 50 years since this happened to me. I know what I experienced and it‚Äôs still just as clear in 
my mind as that day! I have always wondered if being hypnotized would make me re-recall this 
childhood experience again. I have spoken to my husband who is convinced I saw something and is very 
supported of my feelings. I would do this if it‚Äôs a qualified person I‚Äôd like my 
husband to be with me to validate the experience. Not sure if he would participate but he might be 
willing to. We now are retired and living in Florida. I‚Äôm just afraid that someone might suggest ideas that 
might make me forget what I saw. Is this crazy of me to question this? If I do or don‚Äôt do this, I wanted 
to validate this experience with this letter which I will keep a copy in my personal records for my family to read in 
the future. 
I have tried to research if there were any additional sightings in Vermont around this same time, but no 
luck so far. I have yet to find any searches I‚Äôve tried on the internet. I do recall seeing in our local 
newspaper, the Burlington Free Press an article done sometime in the late 80‚Äôs early 90‚Äôs. The article 
stated someone took a black and white photo of a saucer over one of the back dirt roads in Huntington. 
I was in the college or the military at the time, so I don‚Äôt know when or who wrote it. 
I appreciate you allowing me to post my personal experience on your site!

text:
Three bright lights above me that moved independently. 
 
I had just left my friends house on Oster Road, which was located right next to the Knollwood elementary school. I went out the back door of her house and cross the sports field of the school to cut through the playground to take a shortcut to my house on Ferndale Avenue off of Irving Park Boulevard. Their above me were three lights, quite bright, but very high above me. They were not moving and they were positioned in a triangular shape. I immediately got the feeling for no known reason, that they could see me and we‚Äôre watching me. I stood there staring up at them and they started darting around a bit. They moved very quickly but not very far they stayed close to one another. This seemed strange because they were so high up that I knew they had to be moving very very quickly. Then one of them sort of separated itself from the other two and I got fearful that it was going to come down towards me so I just started to run. I was scared out of my mind. What I was saying did not make any sense. The funny thing was I had a difficult time running away, is if my body wanted to stay there in the middle of that field. But for some reason I was able to run even though my body didn‚Äôt seem to really want to. That just might have been fear, I don‚Äôt know.

summary: I thought it was a toy, yellow and blue plastic, as I got closer I was addressed telepathically
stats: Occurred : 11/16/1974 13:00  (Entered as : 11/16/1974 1:00 PM) Reported: 11/19/2022 3:50:14 PM 15:50 Posted: 12/22/2022 Location: Santa Monica, CA Shape: Egg Duration: 30-40 minutes Characteristics: There were lights on the object, The object emitted other objects, The object changed color, The object landed, This is a possible UFO abduction case, Entities were seen, Missing time was experienced
text:
I thought it was a toy, yellow and blue plastic, as I got closer I was addressed telepathically 
 
I was five years old, getting sun as I had just recovered from chicken pox. It was around 1:00 PM on a busy corner in Santa Monica. I saw what looked like an approximately 2 foot tall by 1 foot diameter egg shaped object with rotating lights, red, blue green, purple, and yellow. I felt it was trying to get my attention. I wanted to pick it up and take it home, I was so excited to have found this brand new toy. 
As I was about to pick my new toy up, a monotone electronic sounding male voice in my head said "Hi Meeshell, we're here for you, please don't touch our craft" I felt very scared. I thought someone was playing a prank on me. They asked me a lot of questions and I answered with visions or pictures in my head. They told me that they could trust me and I was an important person to help them. 
As I looked closer I saw that within the egg shaped object there was a rotating middle portion which was blue and had rotating picrures of what I now know looked like grey aliens with big eyes and skinny. At the time I had no knowledge of aliens or ufos. They were very polite but I was scared nonetheless and I basically froze. 
They told me no need to be scared at all and that I was chosen. They said that they would be watching me from now on and would visit. They were reading my thoughts, and I was thinking gift as proof of loyalty. They said "a gift" and a drawbridge came down and a small maybe 2" door slid open right to left The surface had previously been seamless. A small maroon egg shaped object with thick chrome colored wire wrapped around the middle and a tab bent up at one end of the wire rolled down the ramp. I picked it up no idea what it was. 
The said something like here it is. 
I started running fast to my Mom's apartment, sadly she was not there. I went to her friends house where I found her. I showed them the gift and handed it to my Mom's friend. She said "What is this, where did you get this?". I began to explain my encounter that had just happened. 
She started trying to open the gift. The metal wire was pliable and seemed almost liquid like mercury. She twisted opposite directions top and bottom, it opened and she pulled out a string of rice paper elephants in a line trunk to tail. She was happy for me and said it was very special and that they trusted me enough to show themselves. The gift somehow was lost eventually and I have never been able to locate it again. 
I started Montessori school shortly after this incident, and was obsessed with painting and drawing the egg shaped object but never tried to explain what it was to anyone in fear of being ridiculed.

summary: Disc shaped craft hovering over power station
stats: Occurred : 6/2/1978 23:59  (Entered as : 06/02/1978 11:59 PM) Reported: 10/30/2022 12:20:33 PM 12:20 Posted: 12/22/2022 Location: Tacoma, WA Shape: Disk Duration: 10 minutes
text:
Disc shaped craft hovering over power station 
 
While driving southbound on Pearl street around midnight I caught an image of what appeared to be a craft hovering over a power station on 26th street. I pulled into a gas station across the street and got out of my car to view it. It was directly across the street from the gas station above the power station and I could see it clearly. It was metallic and disc shaped. I could see the entire craft. It had no lights and made no sounds. After a few minutes the craft silently moved in my direction and then headed east directly above the power lines. It changed course to southbound Pearl Street and slowly headed down the street directly above the road. 
I jumped in my car and raced to catch up with it which was pretty easy as it was only flying at around 45 miles an hour. I followed it as it flew maybe 50 feet above my car and 50 feet out in front of it. It changed course by flying eastbound on 11th street which I followed closely. After a short distance it angled upwards and shot up into the sky at an extremely fast speed. Within 1-2 seconds it was out of sight. I reported it to the Tacoma police and the dispatcher said they had several calls and asked if I wouldnt mind talking to an officer which I complied. The officer and his partner met me at a 7-11 oarking lot on Pearl street. Unfortunately they did not take me seriously and pretty much laughed at me. Oh well it was not surprising. I live in a different state now but whenever I visit relatives in Tacoma I visit the spot. The power station as well as the gas station which changed hands are still there.

summary: Unknown aircraft nav-anticollision light configuration.
stats: Occurred : 10/11/2019 19:30  (Entered as : 10/11/19 19:30) Reported: 11/4/2019 3:36:19 PM 15:36 Posted: 12/1/2019 Location: Ponce de Leon, FL Shape: Unknown Duration: Characteristics: There were lights on the object
text:
Unknown aircraft nav-anticollision light configuration. 
 
I was looking out my back door window at the stars about 7:30 tonight. 
 
The sky was clear and moonless.  I noticed a bright white light in the sky moving toward me from the south (from the direction of Eglin AFB). 
 
At first, I thought it might be a satellite, then I decided it was more likely an aircraft landing light and walked outside to get a better look.  There are no airports close enough to my location that at pilot would find it necessary to turn on a landing light, so I‚Äôm thinking that maybe the pilot forgot to turn it off after takeoff. 
 
As is typical when seeing an aircraft approaching with the landing light on, the brightness of the white light overpowers the marker lights, with the exception of the strobes, but I didn't see any strobes or beacons, just the brilliant white light. 
 
I estimated the altitude to be between 5 & 10 thousand feet, traveling 200 knots or less as it passed by a couple of miles or less west of my observation point.  My property is surrounded by trees 50 feet or higher, so, from my vantage point, my viewing angle of the craft was about 45 degrees, well above the tree tops. 
 
Unfortunately, my place is too close to I-10 and it was abnormally noisy tonight, so I was unable to hear the aircraft.  But judging from the ambient noise level, I'd guess it wasn't prop driven.  I could have heard a helicopter, and I think I could have heard props as well, but those new jet turbofan engines are really quiet, especially at the slower speed the aircraft was traveling. 
 
The first thing that struck me as odd as it grew closer and was positioned adjacent to me - the intensity of the bright white light remained the same, and did so until it went out of my sight continuing on its flight path northward. 
 
Obviously not a landing light.  At least, I've never seen an omnidirectional, steady-burning bright white light on an aircraft.  But it was close enough as it flew past that I could see four red lights well forward of the bright white light. 
 
Assuming an FAA standard aircraft navigation and anticollision light configuration, I should have been able to see a green marker light on the starboard (right) side of the aircraft, and either a white wingtip strobe, or a red or white strobe or flashing beacon on the lower fuselage, and a red or white strobe or flashing beacon on the upper fuselage or on the tip of the vertical stabilizer.  There also should have been a smaller, white tail light as well.  I should not have been able to see the solid red light, which is supposed to be displayed on the port (left) side of the aircraft. 
 
I didn‚Äôt see any beacons or strobes, red or white.  However, I saw a steady-burning red light out in front (what I assumed was the tip of the nose of the aircraft), and three steady-burning red lights behind the forward red light. 
 
In the 60+ years that I have been aware of, and fascinated by, aircraft, I've never encountered a light configuration like this on an aircraft.  And considering the non-standard light configuration, I was unable to determine the shape of the aircraft. 
 
I‚Äôve been a private pilot since 1982, I was an avionics tech in the USAF for six years, a field engineer with a defense contractor on the USAF/Navy air combat training (ACMI/TACTS) ranges for nine years, and a Nav/Com/Weather technician for the FAA for 25 years.  I retired from the FAA in 2014 and am currently working as a resident engineer for an FAA contractor.

summary: 25-30 white pulsating objects with red glow moving North to South viewed in University Place, WA
stats: Occurred : 10/12/2019 20:19  (Entered as : 10/12/2019 20:19) Reported: 10/12/2019 10:24:11 PM 22:24 Posted: 12/1/2019 Location: University Place, WA Shape: Egg Duration: 12 minutes Characteristics: There were lights on the object, There was an aura or haze around the object
text:
25-30 white pulsating objects with red glow moving North to South viewed in University Place, WA 
 
MULTIPLE UFO SIGHTING October 12, 2019 20:19 HOURS UNIVERSITY PLACE, WASHINGTON  This evening while taking out the trash I and my wife observed numerous objects, all shaped the same, low in the Eastern sky traveling slowly from North to South with slowly pulsating white lights and a reddish glow around the perimeter. 
 
As our house is situated on a Western downhill slope facing the Puget Sound the objects seemed to rise into view from the North and proceed in a relatively quick manner to the South. The objects made no sound that could be discerned from our location.  As the objects proceeded South, they would eventually dim and disappear. 
 
It was a quiet evening with clear skies with a high ceiling.  Where we live is near Joint Base Lewis McChord and we are very familiar with the various aircraft that fly in the area skies and the sounds associated with the aircraft used by the base.  These objects were not rotary or fixed wing aircraft using the regular flight paths as when they do there IS a discernable sound that can be heard for many miles. 
 
If the objects were a considerable distance away then their transit from North to South was pretty rapid and their disappearance was as though they went into a cloud bank however, after discussing the disappearance with my wife, we both agreed that they faded and blinked out. 
 
This event lasted for about 10-12 minutes and consisted of approximately 25, to as high as 30 objects. I took two still photographs and nearly three minutes of video of the event.  I thought that I had captured more of the event unfortunately, when I switched from camera to video, I neglected to start the recording. 
 
I am a retired Firefighter/Paramedic and very used to seeing unusual things, events or situations and accurately documenting my observations.  This is a first for my wife and me.  We hope that this was not some kind of hoax perpetrated in celebration of Halloween resulting in a colossal waste of time and resources.

summary: While driving south on 183, I looked out my drivers window and saw a chevron shaped craft with about 5-6 lights on the bottom of craft.
stats: Occurred : 6/26/1982 21:30  (Entered as : 06/26/1982 9:30 PM) Reported: 10/24/2022 10:59:18 AM 10:59 Posted: 12/22/2022 Location: Fort Worth, TX Shape: Chevron Duration: 10 Minutes Characteristics: There were lights on the object, The object made a sound
text:
While driving south on 183, I looked out my drivers window and saw a chevron shaped craft with about 5-6 lights on the bottom of craft. 
 
I stopped on the shoulder and got out of my car. The craft was about 100 feet off the ground, moving very slow. It was traveling about walking speed. It was moving north in the direction of the runway at Carswell. AFB. It was about 150 to 200 feet across. The only sound was a humming sound like one might hear in a bad amplifier/speaker. 
I watched the craft as it crossed over me and Hwy 183 going in the direction of the base. The craft was very dark and the shape mostly was discerned by the fact it was blocking the stars as it passed. It was opaque as it completely blocked the light of the stars. I do not recall the color of the lights. They were solid and did not flash. Maybe about a foot or so in diameter. They were evenly spaced on the bottom side of the craft. 
As the craft passed over going to the direction of the runway, it started to fade from my view. 
 
On the west side of the AFB is a Lockheed Martin facility. My thinking was that this was some kind if prototype aircraft for the military because of the location. 
I had forgotten about it over the years until I saw some shows about the chevron crafts over Scottsdale AZ and the ones over the Hudson valley. What I saw look almost just as these. The witnesses on the show said they did not hear any sound. As stated, I did hear a low frequency humming sound. 
I call my sighting a craft because I could clearly see and hear it and because of its proximity to the Air force base and Lockheed. But since I have not seen any military plane like it since I will have to identify it as a U F O. 
It does look some what like the chevron shaped stealth plane. But I am sure the stealth plane does not fly this slow or with only a humming sound. 
 
At the time of the sighting I was an Air force reservist on my monthly training at Carswell. I do not recall if I was on my way to the hotel at the time, but I think so. I completed 7 years in the Army and then was in the Air force reserves. At the time I was in the reserve I was also working as an electrician. I currently am retired and worked as an Engineer for 26 years.

summary: Massive black ‚Äúship‚Äù moving slowly about 3X tree height above ground. Black ‚Äúbattleship‚Äù floating silently with some lights.
stats: Occurred : 11/8/1984 20:00  (Entered as : 11/08/1984 8:00 PM) Reported: 12/8/2022 8:37:46 PM 20:37 Posted: 12/22/2022 Location: Brewster, NY Shape: Unknown Duration: 10 minutes Characteristics: There were lights on the object, There was an aura or haze around the object, The object made a sound
text:
Massive black ‚Äúship‚Äù moving slowly about 3X tree height above ground. Black ‚Äúbattleship‚Äù floating silently with some lights. 
 
I was in high school and driving home from visiting a friend. This was the normal route we took and it‚Äôs about 2 miles from our parents house. I was in the vehicle with my brother. As we drove along the edge of the reservoir where the water cascades down I noticed something massive In the sky just two or three tree heights in the air. I screamed out loud to my brother, ‚Äúpull over, pull over!‚Äù I remember that we stopped the car and actually crossed the road we were heading north at the time and we cross the road to a grassy area on the east side of the road adjacent to the reservoir spillway. To this day I can remember the feeling in my chest of anxiety and anticipation and excitement that something bizarre was happening and I jumped out of the car and I can remember my brother getting a little nervous as he screamed ‚Äúwhat the hell are you doing?‚Äú 
 
I looked up and there it was this massive dark form against the night sky blocking out any stars so it came right over us and it seemed as though we could reach up and touch it. If you asked me what its shape was it was too close to us that I did not see it at a distance initially I sought just from below and it seem to have girders and sheep to this massive battleship sized ‚Äúship.‚Äú. It was eerie because there was no significant sound. I remember it having a low humming sound very low and not too loud but my brother remembers it as totally silent. When I say battleship it‚Äôs because I had spent time at the time in my life in Boy Scouts visiting the battleship Massachusetts in fall river. So I had some sense of the scale and this thing was gigantic. Essentially it was impossible what I was looking at it was something that couldn‚Äôt exist a battleship sized object floating quietly above our heads just seemingly above the tree line. It was traveling in the same direction we were so when we jumped out it was just coming over us from south to north and as we stood there at the edge of the reservoir it started to turn and head west in a northwesterly direction, somewhat toward the village of Brewster. I do remember it having some kind of glowing lights on it but that was not a memorable aspect they were too blurry or something. And that seems to be the primary characteristic that I remember is that the shape of the object and the lights were blurry and when you looked directly at them you couldn‚Äôt make out the particular shape even though there was angular form in this dark mass as if it was a metal structure of some kind and it did have lights. Then only five minutes after standing there the thing was already halfway across the reservoir and turned more sharply to the west and just headed in that direction sort of toward Carmel New York. 
 
My brother and I rushed home and promptly told our parents what we had witnessed and it didn‚Äôt even disrupt their television watching for the evening. I remember feeling a strange sense of dreaminess about this event when we told friends and other people and at the time we knew no one and found no one who had shared the experience. As the years of passed thanks to YouTube I have discovered the Hudson Valley UFOs. This includes a piece from unsolved mysteries television show which refers to Dennis Sant, A local public officials who I remember as a child was in my father‚Äòs circles. Here‚Äôs a count of the ship including some of the re-creations on the show really woke me up to the realization that I had not dreamt of this experience. Because you do question after all the years whether it actually happened when there is no feedback mechanism as there is today with social media. I have since searched the Internet and YouTube extensively and watched many videos that people uploaded. They are harder to fine today but around 10 years ago there were easier to find and more plentiful on YouTube and many a persons VHS tapes were shared and I definitely felt that that was the object that we had experienced even though there was some differences in the lights and the actual shape.

summary: Low flying, comet shaped craft, lit like fire, moving in a serpentine motion, changing directions frequently, sometimes disappearing.
stats: Occurred : 5/14/1994 18:00  (Entered as : 05/14/1994 6:00 PM) Reported: 10/27/2022 11:16:51 AM 11:16 Posted: 12/22/2022 Location: Shoreline, WA Shape: Other Duration: Several minutes Characteristics: The object left a trail, There was an aura or haze around the object, The object changed color
text:
Low flying, comet shaped craft, lit like fire, moving in a serpentine motion, changing directions frequently, sometimes disappearing. 
 
We were in high-school, going to the beach in the late afternoon, early evening. My friend and I were several feet behind the group. Only we noticed the craft. It was low over the water, shaped like a Comet, round at the front, tapering to a pointed tail. It looked like it was on fire, like rolling flames, not like a sparkler. It was multiple shades of orange and yellow, like fire. It moved in a serpentine motion in all directions. It would snake thru the air horizontally, nearly stop, make a right hand turn, and start snaking vertically thru the sky, then shift again snaking back the other way. It was so unnatural that we were shocked. We tried catching up to the rest of the group to tell them to look. Every time we caught up it would disappear. We'd drop back, talking about it, then it'd reappear, snaking thru the sky in multiple direction. Every time we tried to reach our friends to have them look it'd blink out of sight again. The sky was clear, it was late. The sun was low, but no clouds or other interference was blocking our view. It lasted seceral minutes, and we were just shocked. I remember it clear as day, and I've never seen another object on earth look or move the way that flying craft looked or moved. This happened before internet, so there was no one to report to. And before smart phones, so we had no camera on hand. We both saw the exact same thing and discussed it for quite a while as we watched it. We were sober, the object was fairly close, as the Puget Sound is not very wide. You can see land across the Sound, so we could tell the object was over the water, somewhere between our beach and the opposite beach. It was fairly low In the sky, and so close we could see the surface lit up like fire, but I dont believe it was actually fire. It wasnt dark yet, not even dusk, but just before sunset I think. To this day I'm convinced it was an otherworldly craft due to its appearance and physics defying movement thru the sky. Almost like it was swimming, but thru the air.
