summary: Craft of unknown origins hovering about the Model Basin
stats: Occurred : 6/1/1995 23:00  (Entered as : 06/01/1995 11:00 PM) Reported: 10/25/2022 1:19:33 PM 13:19 Posted: 12/22/2022 Location: Potomac, MD Shape: Egg Duration: 5 minutes Characteristics: There were lights on the object, Animals reacted to the event
text:
Craft of unknown origins hovering about the Model Basin 
 
When I was 16 or 17, so 1994 to 1995, I was driving home late at night along the Clara Barton parkway. I was heading towards Potomac from Bethesda or NW DC, and it was nearing my curfew, so somewhere after 11 and before midnight, I believe. As I came out from the underpass (495 crosses over the parkway near here), the Model Basin came into view, as normal. What was not normal: a silvery, blimp or more accurately, burger? chipwich? shaped thing was hovering over the Basin. It appeared to be lit from within, or rather, that it had a luminescence about it. I can't recall any blinking lights, though I recall it had sort of a nubbly shape along the edges, which maybe were lights. It was very large, and terrified teenaged me. I floored it, trying to create as much space as possible between this....craft...and myself. It was super big in the rearview mirror, and it was quiet. I heard nothing, not even the usual chirping crickets or tree frogs that infest the forests along the parkway. As I sped (I drove a thunderbird, and I floored it, I was waaaaay over the speed limit), I anxiously watched it continue to hover. 
 
I know what blimps look like. I know what a lot of jets, ships, planes, fighters, etc look like. I grew up here, and you see a lot of stuff. This was nothing commercial, and wasn't a weather balloon or blimp, though it hovered similarly. It didn't resemble any space shuttle or stealth jet I've seen. It was just...totally foreign to my mind. It's feasible it was some other country's spy tech, but the silence confused me-I still can recall that detail 25 years later. 
 
The next day or so later, I was talking to a friend about it while we got coffee. A woman approached me and stated she'd spotted it as well, and called it in (not sure who she called, but she reported it) and was informed it was a weather balloon. She said it was not a weather balloon, her brother worked as a meteorologist and she knew what they looked like. To date, this is the only person I've ever encountered who saw it, and I've never seen any other references to it aside from my own posts here and there. 
 
Date is approximate as there was no internet site to log this stuff on back then. I am 100% sure it was prior to 1997, and based on the car I was driving, it would place it between Jan 10, 1994 to August 1995.

summary: 2 brights stars. First 1, then 2. Then none.
stats: Occurred : 10/1/1996 19:00  (Entered as : 10/01/1996 7:00 PM) Reported: 10/20/2022 9:51:10 PM 21:51 Posted: 12/22/2022 Location: Salinas, Canelones Department Shape: Light Duration: 20 minutes
text:
2 brights stars. First 1, then 2. Then none. 
 
UFO happened in Salinas, slightly rural area, Uruguay 1996, just going on dark and on the spare property of mis abuelos. I was wanting to take a photo of this beautiful big bright star that caught my attention (I had grabbed my Olympus wind up camera and walked into the middle of the empty property). On the corner of my eye it would shake around. I thought 'bizarre' and looked up and it went still - but I felt like it was mocking me strangely ?. I lifted my camera to take the photo and it did it again. It would be still but shake around when I held the camera up. At first I thought 'oh, ok, the lens in the camera can't make focus at such a distance' - but it wasn't shaking through my lens, only when I actioned to focus my camera it would shake. A feeling of being mocked was starting to weigh on me. A little perplexed, I tried different settings on the camera and this happened 4-5 times until the last time I took the camera away, it continued to shake around in the high heavens above. Then it would stop and start and move around the sky - do a shake and stop. 
On the ground looking up - it was shaking around 2 cm either way but this would have been a huge magnitude in the sky. I looked over to my grandparents place wondering to go over and call for them to come see or are my eyes affected somehow, at the same time I thought I might loose this phenomenon, I'll stay ?. I would look to the ground to make sure my eyes were not playing up but my eye sight and everything was normal except this big bright star. I rubbed my eyes, I patted them. I then looked up and it zoomed left - paused, then zoomed right - then paused. A smaller, colourful one appeared zooming in (bright with reddish / pink-green outer colour (not all the way round, just to two sides) zoom up close to the one I was watching (which was paused at this time), it came from the west, paused, did a shake, paused and took off in a split second. I thought 'ok, I'm not seeing things because now there's 2, the larger one is clearly not shaking and the newer one is. I can't remember where it took off but it zoomed off fast and I didn't want to loose sighting of the bigger one by following or searching for the littler one. Then the one I had been focusing on, zoomed to the south-east a little (20cm - ground measurement), stopped approx 5-10 seconds, shook about as of to say 'bye' I think, then took off south and disappeared. I was left there looking back at where this star initially sat, and why I was there - well, I was there to take a photo of this big bright star' and was now left with nothing. Nothing sat in the place in the sky of where this big bright star was approx 10 - 20 minutes ago. I looked to the south and waited, nothing. I walked back over the fence and told no-one. I printed my photos - and there it is, a shaken star. But I hope I still have it. I can't explain anything else. I know what drove me to pick up my camera, walk over to take a picture of this big bright star, now I walked back with no big bright star in its place in the sky, and baffled to what just happened.

summary: My wife, kids and I witnessed a V formation of six copper colored objects that crossed the entire sky in a few seconds.
stats: Occurred : 3/13/1997 21:30  (Entered as : 03/13/1997 9:30 PM) Reported: 11/4/2022 1:31:01 PM 13:31 Posted: 12/22/2022 Location: Gaithersburg, MD Shape: Formation Duration: 10 seconds or less
text:
My wife, kids and I witnessed a V formation of six copper colored objects that crossed the entire sky in a few seconds. 
 
On the evening of March 13, 1997 I wanted to take my wife and kids outside to try and view the Hale-Bopp comet. I had an astronomy class in college and had a telescope as a kid and have always been interested in astronomy. I think the time was about 9:30 pm. Our home was located on a small hill on a large lot with an open view of the sky. When we tried to spot the comet we all witnessed a V formation of six coppery colored objects directly above us at about the twelve o'clock position, moving east to west, cross the sky in a few seconds. These objects looked very high up in the sky since the formation looked very small. My kids were a little shook up because they knew we witnessed something very unusual. A few days or weeks later we learned that the Phoenix lights took place the same evening. We have no idea if the two events are related but it's very coincidental. It's taken me a long time to write a report on this but at the time I didn't know about NUFORC or even if a report could be filed. Sometimes I wonder if these UFOs want to be seen and know when humans are viewing them.

summary: Saw a red long blinking light in a holler, bobbing side to side, spotlit craft and then slowly over me, & shot like bullet outta view
stats: Occurred : 6/28/1997 03:00  (Entered as : 06/28/1997 3:00 AM) Reported: 11/2/2022 10:15:27 PM 22:15 Posted: 12/22/2022 Location: Almartha, MO Shape: Triangle Duration: 10 minutes or so Characteristics: There were lights on the object
text:
Saw a red long blinking light in a holler, bobbing side to side, spotlit craft and then slowly over me, & shot like bullet outta view 
 
I was out on highway road hunting and saw what I thought was a radio tower slowly blinking, until I realized it was in a holler below my vantage point on top of hill. Noticed it was slowly moving small movements side to side, so after watching it for about 5 minutes, I grabbed my spotlight out of truck. I lit it up, was some kind of aircraft about 25-30 feet wide & around 8-9 feet thick, looked to be a triangle shape with rounded tips, and on the sides of the points there where backlit red crystal like panels strobing slowly. I noticed it was extremely quiet running, was around 15 feet off the ground, and the trees & grasses beneath it seemed to be gently blowing around. After about 10-15 seconds of it spotlighted, it raised out of the holler, came at me, went over me about 20-30 feet above me, with spotlight I could make out ribbed hoses running half-spherically across the bottom of it, it was all flat black, and the thing vibrated the hell out of me as it passed over like a giant sonic toothbrush feeling. It continued to move away from me to the west, I could see approximately 60 miles, but once it was a quarter mile away it shot off out of my 60 mile view in 2-3 seconds. I used to assume it was something from Whiteman's AFB that flies aircraft thru there often & originally called them to ask if anything was flying thru there in that timeframe and they said no, but I figured they probably would've said that either way honestly. I've never seen anything like it before that night, nor since - but would like to know what it might've been tho.

text:
((NUFORC Note:  This report submitted as an e-mail, and copied here.  PD)) 
 
I would like to submit this detailed report of a sighting that took place on Wednesday, September 3, 1997.  Because what I saw was so unusual, I have taken the time to document the details of the event so as to provide serious UFO researchers with accurate information.  I would be interested in any information you may have regarding similar sightings and if there are any terrestrial aircraft fitting this description.  Please feel free to write or contact me by phone or E-mail.   I have also submited a report electronicly. 
 
Date of sighting:	 9/3/97  Time of sighting:	11:10 PM 
 
Description Of Sighting 
I had just returned home and was standing in my driveway to look up at the stars before entering the house.  It was a very clear, moonless night and the stars were very bright.  As I was looking up at constellations in the east, a moving triangular object caught my eye.  I turned and watched as it glided swiftly across the sky in front of me.  What made it visible were neon-like strips of blue-green light that traced the outer edges of the craft.  I was amazed at how the light wrapped around the pointed nose and the two back corners.  There were also strips of this blue-green light along the side and back.  There were no other lights but these on the craft. The lights glowed dimly and had there been a full moon or bright city lights near by, I doubt that it would have been visible.  Although I could not make out the details of the objects surface, the fact that the light strips traced the outline of a long triangular object was unmistakable.  The changing perspective of the outline of light as it traversed the night sky was also consistent with a three dimensional object. The night was very quiet and no sound was detectable.  I watched until it went behind a tree that blocked it from view as it continued in a north eastern direction.  This UFO was traveling very fast in a straight line at a low altitude.   
 
Page 1 of 2 
 
Details of Sighting; 
 
Conditions		 
Clear, moonless, quiet, no wind 
 
Size & Position 
The size of the object in the sky was almost as large as a full moon.  The altitude was much lower than that a commercial jet.  Its‚Äô position in the sky was about a 45 degree angle from the ground.          
 
 
Speed 
Much faster that a commercial jet.  I would not say that it ‚Äúshot‚Äù across the sky, but that it ‚Äúglided swiftly‚Äù 
 
Direction of Travel 
It came from the south west and continued traveling in a north eastern direction. 
 
Sound 
Silent, no sound detected 
 
Location of Sighting 
Suburban, residential, at edge of town, no street lights, dark skies.

heading south east on Route 60 (towards new kent county) on the way to the church that hosted my Thursday night boyscout meetings.. to the right of me(passenger, I was either 12 or 13 years old when this happened) on the side of route 60 the road is lined with trees/forrest and there was some lights flashing between the trees as we proceeded down the road(at roughly 55mph) the lights kept pace with the vehicle i was in(i assumed this was probably a helicopter) for a few seconds maybe 30 seconds, then it started to move ahead of us while still behind the tree line, raised up(im not sure about this, it may have been this high already) and literally just over the tree line a perfect triangle of white lights proceeded to cross over the road in front of us, in which it then stayed stationary over the highway and started to rotate(this part I am not sure if it was rotating clockwise or counter clockwise) and it did this as we passed under it and I turned around and watched it keep rotating, we turned to the road with the church and i lost sight of it.. it was dead silent, the uner of the object, the triangle was darker than the sky above it.. there is a army base and a big international airport(RIC) to the south of where I was

text:
Saw 3 craft go straight up and each had this explosion of light as it disappeared into outer space. 
 
Got home from night church in Austin Tx., and had to pull closed the blinds. That‚Äôs when I noticed how bright the stars were, so I went outside. Well these 3 stars were moving. For a quick second, I thought I was getting dizzy as stars don‚Äôt move. But these 3 did, very slowly in a straight line. Then they all 3 came to a stop. Then the 1st one shot straight up, extremely fast. It was pretty big because I could see it for a long way, and I thought they were stars after all. But when it was almost out of view, there was this huge explosion of light, which quickly faded, along with the star. My first thought was, I saw it leave our magnetosphere, which caused that light. Then I looked back down at the other 2, and the next one did the same thing. When it was gone, the last one left. Since I was busy looking up, I can‚Äôt tell you if the other 2 moved forward, and took off in the exact same place as the first one, or if they all just went up where they had stopped. (I was reading about wormholes, so that info would have been helpful.) While this was 24 years ago, I have written about this experience many many times since. I didn‚Äôt know your organization existed until today.

stats: Occurred : 8/25/1999 04:00  (Entered as : 08/25/1999 4:00 AM) Reported: 10/20/2022 2:04:29 PM 14:04 Posted: 12/22/2022 Location: Knoxville, TN Shape: Light Duration: 10 to 20 seconds Characteristics: There were lights on the object, The object left a trail, The object changed color
text:
Large set of lights, probably one craft, similar to something from CE of the 3rd kind 
 
Sighting occurred appx 4am in the last week of August 1999. I was staying with a friend who lived in my neighborhood at the time. We were sky watching and something caught our eyes, a set of lights in the northern part of the sky that looked to be a single craft. The lights were various colors, mostly what I would call jewel tones, or showing the spectrum of the colors of the rainbow. Some of these colors appeared to possibly be changing or rotating through colors quickly, maybe a few dozen individual lights in the rough shape of an oval. The object hovered in one place and the sighting lasted for about 20 seconds and it shot of vertically and also quickly faded like maybe it was cloaking. As any FYI--weather was calm, sky was clear, no wind, no other objects in the sky, no sound coming from the object. Its size was indeterminate as well as distance, as it was a night sighting without anything nearby to compare it to (my guess is an object a few dozen yards across at approximately few hundred feet above the ground). My friend and I were noticeably shaken by the event, as it gave us both a chill all the way down our spines. I had seen other objects before this event and since then, but none as memorable.

3 white Orbs/Spheres

‚Ä¢ Only sounds were my idling vehicle and one GPU in the distance. 
‚Ä¢ Estimate diameter at 50 feet, all 3 were same size 
‚Ä¢ Estimate distance away 2k-5k feet and 2k-5k feet in altitude 
‚Ä¢ Moved in 3 dimensions

summary: Strange object seen in proximity to turboprop aircraft near Spokane, WA.
stats: Occurred : 8/21/2001 20:35 Reported: 8/23/2001 18:35 Posted: 12/22/2022 Location: Spokane (near), WA Shape:
text:
((NUFORC Note:  Copied report submitted via e-message.  PD)) 
 
Date Aug. 21, Time 9:40 P.M. 
  
I am writing in regards to what my husband and I saw tonight. At approximately 8:35 this evening we heard and saw a turboprop aircraft, coming over the horizon from the west.There were no lights on the plane at all. The plane was coming over the top of our place at around 3000 ft. To the left of the plane fairly close, were two small objects with lights red and light yellow or white. Compared to the plane they were quit a bit smaller. I left the back of the house to go to the front to get a better look, when I got to the front yard I saw 5 strobing lights about 500 ft. apart following behind the turboprop. going north east.This time I could not see the objects only the lights, very bright and blinking or strobing red and white or yellow. Then the turbo made a left turn lights following him going west again, all disappeared in the clouds. It was very unusual, and unlike anything I have seen before. We heard the plane several times earlier in the evening but did not go out to look at it so I don't know if the lights were there at that time. There was only the sound from the turboprop aircraft, no other aircraft sounds.  We thought it might be connected with the fires here in eastern Washington.  Since you investigate sightings, I thought you might be able to tell us what you thought the lights were that accompanied that plane. 
  
Thank you, 
((name deleted)) 
 
((ADDENDUM TO ORIGINAL REPORT)) 
 
Hi Peter, 
  
I've spent the morning on the phone.  I was able to speak to the supervisor of Spokane tower and approach control.  He said that they do not cover our area which is north of Evans, WA on Hwy 25 and next to the Columbia River.  However, he was very interested in the details of this phenomena and asked to be kept informed if we were able to establish any further information.  He suggested that contacting Whidbey Island Naval Air Station would probably not produce any results.  I also assume that Seattle Center would not be willing to disclose any information.   
  
A quick bio, I'm ((age deleted)), ((number of thousands of hours deleted)) hours of flying air charter and flight instruction in the Seattle area, but that was over 20 years ago.  And another point I feel should be mentioned is we have had a lot of aircraft activity in this area because of the forest fire on Mount Leona in Ferry County and military aircraft operating in Roosevelt MOA, therefore this started out as not to unusual. 
  
I saw what looked like a Lockheed Martin EP-3E Aries II or similar, but the color was dark olive gray or charcoal brown.  It was flying from west to east about 3000' to 4000' above ground level.  It's location when we first saw it was about 48 degrees and 45 minutes north and 118 degrees and 10 minutes west.  I was moving at normal cruise speed.  It's navigation lights and strobe were off.  It was an unusual aircraft for this area. 
  
My first thought was they were doing a infrared scan of the fire area.  I did think it strange not to have the nav lights on, especially when we were in the evening transition period with a lot of air traffic in the area.  That's when my wife said there were two other lights beside it.  I moved to a better location to see it.  That's when I saw two very intense strobe lights flashing red and white.  One of them moved into close-formation on its starboard quarter, less than a 100'.  Then I noticed another strobe light appear next to the outboard one.  I did not see the third light approach, it  just appeared.  I could not hear any noise other than the sound of the turbine engines on the large aircraft.  I couldn't see any physical aircraft near or around the strobe lights.   
  
At this point I had to move to another location to continue to watch.  When I regained a view of them there were four strobe lights flying in an echelon formation from the aircrafts starboard quarter with equal spacing of about 500'.  Then again another strobe light just appeared outside the fourth one.  Then the strangest part started, they began to disappear and reappear over and over again, but in different positions. Or, there were more than five of them, but only five showing at any given time.  Finally, the large aircraft started a gradual left turn, back to the west and shortly disappeared behind the clouds north of us. We stood there thunderstruck. 
  
Peter, I've had two physical sightings in my life time.  The first was in the service and it was a subsurface craft that went directly under our ship and visible.  The second was also on the ocean during a return trip on a 44' racing sailboat 1000' miles north of Hawaii with 8 witnesses, it was larger than an aircraft carrier and about a 1000' from us.  So I'm not new to this game, but this one is a mystery for me.  I don't know what to think.  I'm just reaching out for help in understanding what my wife and I have witnessed.  I had no problem accepting the physical sightings, but this one left me with to many possibilities to consider.  Now I understand why there are so many that start doubting what they really saw because there isn't any hard evidence.  We wish to remain anonymous, however we don't mind you using this information for your research or sharing it with others. 
  
We're watching the sky more closely, 
  
((names deleted))

text:
I witnessed a triangular shaped air craft with 4 lights flying at low altitude with no noise and at slow stall speeds 
 
I work as a night shift security guard. As I was opening the gates to the parking lots I noticed a bright light in the east. In that general direction there is a hospital with a helicopter pad and I could hear helicopter noise so I assumed it was that. The light seemed very bright so I continued to watch it for a minute or two. At that point the helicopter at the hospital took off and broke the tree line. So I know it was not a helicopter at that point. After the noise drowned off the light continued to just sit in its position and I began walking towards the guard shack to get my phone. As I started to move I could see the one light starting to break in 4 lights. It wasn‚Äôt until it was extremely close that I realized it was a shape of a black triangle. With one light at the point, one light in the back middle, and one light left and right from the back middle light in each direction. It was roughly 2000‚Äô off the ground (I used an altitude comparison sheet I! found online because it was very low to make absolutely 0 noise.). It was also going rough 100 mph, I state that liberally because I feel if you could drive a car in a straight line next to it you could easily keep up at 60-70 mph. It had no blinking marker lights to indicate wings or a tail. It did had a singular strobing light underneath that was only visible when it was directly over head. In 2000 there was a black triangle sighting in this town that was chased by three different police departments towards saint Louis, MO before they lost sight of it. There is also an Air Force base within 30 miles from where I worked so I thought maybe it was a plane heading there which might explain the no markers, but I don‚Äôt think it would explain the lack of sound and very slow speeds.. it was coming from the east moving west, slightly north away from the Air Force base as it left my sight of view

summary: A bright white light descended rapidly out of a low hanging cloud in an evening sky.
stats: Occurred : 10/13/2019 19:29  (Entered as : 10/13/19 19:29) Reported: 10/13/2019 5:41:44 PM 17:41 Posted: 12/1/2019 Location: Naples, FL Shape: Cone Duration: 10 seconds Characteristics: There were lights on the object, There was an aura or haze around the object, The object made a sound, There were aircraft in the vicinity or aircraft chasing the object, Animals reacted to the event
text:
A bright white light descended rapidly out of a low hanging cloud in an evening sky. 
 
I happened to look up at a fast moving cone shaped object descending rapidly out of a low hanging cloud. The sky was blocked out by these low clouds. The sun either had already set or was blocked out by these grey low hanging clouds. There was approximately 35% ambient light remaining at the moment of the sighting. The clouds were at 1500 ft and broken. Some clouds were higher some lower but blocking out the evening sky. This object as I said dropped rapidly to approximately 500 ft elevation. It hovered there for 3 seconds then, It flew rapidly to the right, stopped after traveling about 30 degrees across a 180 degree field of view. After traveling quickly across that distance it stopped abruptly, held position for 3 seconds and reversed direction. It flew back in the direction from which it came as it gained altitude. It made several quick upward maneuvers as it traveled never changing shape as an aircraft would as it would turn to, or away from you as it m! aneuvered. It then stopped abruptly again. Hovered for an instant then it moved back to the right, as it very rapidly descended downward out of my field of view. It never reappeared in 5 minutes as I continued to scan the evening sky. I happened to be walking my dog and my dog alerted me to it, which began my sighting. My dog was frightened by the sight and she immediately turned around and headed back to the house we had come from 30 seconds before. It made a very faint humming sound as it maneuvered. It was cone shaped and seemed as though a bright whitish green light was suspended below the cone. It had what appeared to be a bright white light at the apex of the cone. These lights never changed their relative position as it sped around the sky. I am a 66 year old man. I have excellent uncorrected vision. I am a licensed Private Pilot and not prone to rash judgements. I have never made a UFO report before and frankly didnt want to report this one. I don't want attention or publicity for this sighting. Being a Pilot I do Not want to go on record as having witnessed this UFO.  I felt duty bound to report this sighting so as to add my report to any others that might be made in response to this sighting.

summary: Triangle shaped craft over Edmonton International/ HWY 2
stats: Occurred : 10/14/2019 00:25  (Entered as : 10/14/19 00:25) Reported: 10/19/2019 4:32:38 AM 04:32 Posted: 12/1/2019 Location: Edmonton HWY 2 Southbound, AB Shape: Triangle Duration: 1 minute Characteristics: There were lights on the object
text:
Triangle shaped craft over Edmonton International/ HWY 2 
 
As I was driving southbound on Queen Elizabeth HWY 2, roughly 2/3 kms north of the Leduc overpass for the airport, to meet a friend for a pick up at the Edmonton International Airport (YEG) I noticed flashing lights above the road ahead of me. They were red and blue if I'm not mistaken but the fog made it difficult to see very far. As I continued I noticed a distinct triangular shape to the flying object and as it got closer I noticed it was quite close to the ground for a plane, less than 50 feet from the ground. The craft passed directly over me and thanks to my large panoramic sunroof I was able to see the bottom of the object as it passed overhead. Unfortunately the time of night made making out any details other than its overall triangle shape almost impossible. I did notice one thing though, how extremely quiet it was. Not a single noise was made as it passed (I turned down all my radio as it was approaching). I've worked at this airport in the past as! well as others in the area and if a plane or any engine would to pass by at this distance you would absolutely hear it. I hope others have seen this, I'm just trying to make sense of it.

summary: Up close sighting of the supposed Gimbal ufo
stats: Occurred : 7/28/2003 19:46  (Entered as : 07/28/2003 7:46 PM) Reported: 10/22/2022 4:35:10 AM 04:35 Posted: 12/22/2022 Location: Wallasey, Wirral Shape: Disk Duration: 1 minute
text:
Up close sighting of the supposed Gimbal ufo 
 
Back in 2004. I was around 14 at the time. 
 
The disk like craft was up in the Sky about 100 yards away from my house. As I looked at it, it approached the house to take a turn over the gardens attaching our house to the one behind it. 
 
It paused at the window where I was looking at it for a good 20 or so seconds. During this time I had a clear view of the craft. 
 
It was a disk that had edging on a slight upwardly linear gradient. On the top and bottom were tower like structures made from something black that looked like hard silicone but a metal‚Ä¶ slightly porous maybe? (imagine a three legged based Eiffel Tower that was been twisted but the gaps in between are not linear and seem random - difficult to explain this form as it‚Äôs not something we see in our typical design patterns) and the central disc was emanating very bright light but it did not light up the surroundings of the craft. The light was blocked from exiting the craft. 
 
The tower like structures were stable and not moving but the central disc was rotating. It was initially rotating right but as it came to take the left turn it stopped rotating as it hovered outside my house before then rotating left as it shot off from 0 to whatever it was. 
 
Call it sixth sense or just an remnant of our evolution but when it first stopped I had the ‚Äòinner feeling‚Äô as though whatever was inside did not see me but this changed and suddenly the feeling of being noticed was experienced. At this point the craft took off.

summary: Didn't think much of this until now...
stats: Occurred : 6/6/2005 23:30  (Entered as : 06/06/2005 11:30 PM) Reported: 11/2/2022 8:08:36 AM 08:08 Posted: 12/22/2022 Location: Saraland, AL Shape: Triangle Duration: 5-10 minutes
text:
Didn't think much of this until now... 
 
This was in approximately early summer of 2005, so it was almost 17 1/2 years ago, but I remember it fairly clearly. I believe it was early summer because I remember a friend and I were in my above-ground pool late at night. No one else was home, as the rest of the family had taken a cruise that week. I stayed behind because I was working two jobs and couldn't take off. The neighborhood was very dark, very still and very quiet - so much so that we were nearly whispering when we talked because talking in a normal voice seemed like we were yelling. We were just relaxing and enjoying the evening (it was a clear evening - no clouds), when suddenly I became aware of some type of aircraft that was (very) slowly approaching us. I remember being stunned because 1. It was flying extremely low - barely above treetop level (75 ft. pine trees). 2. It was SILENT. Zero noise. That's what freaked me out more than anything else. 3. It seemed like a very dark gray and had some lights underneath on the edges, but none of the lights were on. My friend and I just froze and I remember feeling like I was trying very hard to hold my breath. I remember feeling frightened because I didn't know what was capable of doing that or if it it saw us. I felt that it did. As it came closer, we both (without discussing it with each other first) sunk down lower into the water and closed our eyes as it passed. When I opened my eyes, it had passed directly over us (was still on the same flight path) and we watched in silence as it passed over three or more houses. We looked at each other for a moment - trying to wordlessly verify that we'd both seen the same thing - and when we glanced back, it was gone. I remember that we were suddenly freezing in the water (when it had seemed warm before. I'm not saying this was a result of the object but perhaps because the experience gave us chills. We got out of the pool and were both shaking almost uncontrollably for an hour after that.) 2005 was really before drones were mainstream (at least, as far as I knew... and certainly before I knew what they were) but at the time I thought surely it was something military related. I remember specifically thinking that it was flying below airspace radar detection levels - something I had either read about or seen on the news in the wake of 9/11 (which is the only way I would have even known that there was such thing). I remember it being large but it certainly wasn't house sized or football field sized. It really freaked us out for a few days - I just had an overall uneasy feeling. It may actually be the first time that I experienced anxiety now that I think about it. My friend and I never talked about it again. I have thought about it fleetingly over the years randomly - thinking wow, that was so strange, but again, never thought much of it. However, I recently watched the latest Unsolved Mysteries episode about UFOs/UAPs and it made me rethink that experience. I googled in an attempt to find other reports of sightings around that time to hopefully verify my recollection. I found this site. I didn't find any in my area, but to my shock, I found many, many, many similar reports. After reading all of the reports on this site, in articles, watching shows, and reading the 2021 pentagon report (with a new report to be released sometime this week), all spanning multiple decades, I'm now a believer. I feel it is important to mention that, while I do enjoy watching Harry Potter and other fantastical shows and movies with my children, I do not believe in real life magic, ghosts, luck, etc. and I am an atheist. And, even after seeing what I saw all those years ago, I did not once think ET beings/vehicles existed until now. There are too many similarities in stories from people who never met each other and are not obviously mentally ill to call it coincidences or delusions. Especially considering that there is no way technology existed in the 40s, 50s, 60s, 70s, 80s or possibly even 90s that would account for the things people have seen. Also, I've seen several mentions about these types of crafts being near interstates. The pool was approximately 421 feet from an interstate. I'm including a google maps screenshot with an annotation I added to show the pool (the yellow highlighted dot) and the direction of flight. I'm also including some photos/renderings I found on this site, the history channel site, and google images. The object seemed almost like a combination of those images to the best of my recollection. 
 
It may be that the event is completely explainable. But, since I've seen so many similar accounts, I thought it was worth reporting.

summary: Silver UFO hovering a few miles from the Robinson Nuclear Plant
stats: Occurred : 7/1/2005 12:00  (Entered as : 07/01/2005 12:00 PM) Reported: 12/17/2022 9:44:42 AM 09:44 Posted: 12/22/2022 Location: Hartsville, SC Shape: Cone Duration: A few minutes.
text:
Silver UFO hovering a few miles from the Robinson Nuclear Plant 
 
This was a few years ago when I was a teenager, so my memory is pretty weak about everything time-related. But my memory of the event is crystal because it has been the only UFO I've seen in my life. 
 
I was riding in the back of my dad's truck. We were coming home from a family visit up in Chesterfield, South Carolina, and I was napping as we went home on the Ruby Road, which runs for miles and miles through Darlington and Chesterfield counties. When we got toward the plant, which was close to home, I opened my eyes and just watched the clouds go along because it was a beautiful summer day (that's why I think it was in July or August). Something silver up in the air caught my attention as we were driving along. When I focused on it, I could clearly see it was much closer to me than the clouds I had been looking at (like superimposed, or like you would see a helicopter in the air and you could judge distance). 
 
The craft itself was bell-shaped. It was very far away, and the truck was moving, but there was a definite curve to the top of it and a flat bit on the bottom. It was very bright, very shiny, and it was just hanging there in the air. I saw it for five or six minutes, and I kept my eyes on it as the truck moved and my position changed, so I'm sure it was just hovering. Dad kept driving and I eventually lost sight of it. 
 
The most interesting thing is that we were close to the Robinson Nuclear Plant. I've never seen anything like it before or since. I just felt like I had to tell someone about this after seeing your interview on the new Missing 411 movie.

summary: The object was metallic, large, cigar shaped with a bright gleam of light emanating from one end almost separate from the craft.
stats: Occurred : 4/11/2007 10:30  (Entered as : 04/11/2007 10:30 AM) Reported: 10/8/2022 8:55:55 PM 20:55 Posted: 12/22/2022 Location: Greenwood, AR Shape: Cigar Duration: 5-10 minutes Characteristics: There were lights on the object, There was an aura or haze around the object, The object emitted other objects, The object emitted beams
text:
The object was metallic, large, cigar shaped with a bright gleam of light emanating from one end almost separate from the craft. 
 
I was only around 8 or 9 years old at the time. The only witness I still have contact with doesn't remember the event. It was recess just after lunch at the swing sets when my friend kept talking about how he could see a UFO and it took me a while to see what he was pointing at. Once my eyes locked in on what I was seeing, it was clear that it was not a plane or a cloud. I was looking directly West and around 80 degrees upwards from the ground. It was a metallic cigar-shaped object. On the left of it, there was a light obscuring it's end where it may have come to a point. The craft was high in the cloudless sky and appeared relatively large and very high in altitude accounting for atmospheric scattering of light (like how a distant object appears slightly blue). It was slowly moving straight up, and as it moved, the light that was emanating from it's left end was pulsating and growing brighter while also dimming and becoming invisible at times. This gave me a chance to really observe the light. The light pulsated in a very distinct pattern that would rotate. It almost seemed to be a physical object while also being very bright. The pattern resembled a typical starlight pattern viewed through an optical device like a telescope. 
As the object continued to ascend, it got so high up that all that was visible was the "light". Eventually, the light was no longer visible. It appeared to have left the atmosphere, entirely. 
My friend said he saw an orb shoot out and was doing weird maneuvers in the sky while my eyes had drifted away. At this point, I was still processing what I just saw, so I didn't see the orb he was talking about but played along as if I did. 
The cigar shaped object never went in a different direction - just up. It was very enticing, and I had a very real urge to follow it somehow. 
Physically, I and my surroundings experienced no effects that I am aware of. I think everyone forgot about it shortly afterwards. 
 
I should note: nothing in this story was exaggerated, fabricated, or left out regarding my entire observation of this object. As far as I know, I am the only witness; however, there may be more witnesses in the area that I just never talked to about. 
 
I am not 100% certain about the date and time, but I had to have been in third or fourth grade at the time (2006-2008). It was warm, not quite hot, cloudless, and before or around noon. The exact coordinates I was standing was 35¬∞13'15.47"N 94¬∞15'20.11"W looking west and upwards.

summary: Visited by the same "craft" on three seperate dates,  just waiting for an explanation
stats: Occurred : 5/15/2007 23:00  (Entered as : 5/07-11/08 23:00) Reported: 9/2/2009 1:21:56 PM 13:21 Posted: 12/22/2022 Location: Gladewater, TX Shape: Unknown Duration: 18 months Characteristics: There were lights on the object
text:
Visited by the same "craft" on three seperate dates,  just waiting for an explanation 
 
Hello UFO Center, hope all is well. Let me start by introducing myself. My name is ***** and I live in Texas with my wife and my son. I am 30 years old, and have had an assortment of occupations in my short time here so far. I started working as a bricklayers helper out of highschool for about three years. From there I managed a Furniture Store warehouse,then worked in technical support for AOL from '99 to '01, back to brick work, then a 5 year stint with the Pepsi Bottling Group, and now am a paramedic for East Texas Medical Center at the age of 30. I'm telling you all this to give you at least some idea of who I am. I met my wife at the age of 17 and have been happily married ever since. I love my family and happily work hard for them. 
 
 FIRST EXPERIENCE  I am writing you because I dont know where else to go. I have been "visited" by an unrecognizable object on three seperate occasions. Now your probably thinking, "Big deal, people have been seeing UFO's since mans beginning." Thats kinda my perspective on the topic. However, four nights ago, a thought came to me that made me wonder why I didnt think it sooner. The thought was, "of all the stories and reports and accounts of "alien encounters", I have never heard of or read about any report that was even close to mine. I am almost hesitant to continue, for I am not sure if you will even read this, but here goes.  I have had countless abnormal experiences in the twilight hours,  but these three are the ones that demand my attention.  Three visitations, the first one around May 22 or 23 of 2007, I was by myself.  We were living in a house in ********* which is a very rural area just outside *********, Tx.  We had moved there in June of '06.  I had quit my job at Pepsi ! in December after my fathers death in November of '06,  and was preparing to start EMT-Basic school in January.  I worked at a telephone operating center while I went to school.  I worked mainly afternoons through nights,  during the slower hours.  This proved advantageous,  as I was able to study and do work in between calls.  I was still working as an operator,  just finishing EMT school. That spring I had discovered information on the mayans and other topics such as Edward Leedskalnins book Magnetic Current,  which sparked interest and curiosity like I had never known.  This was also the time when I started almost mindlessly drawing all these geometrical shapes at work.  I would get in this zone and just drawing all kinds of equilateral triangles and evenly section them off and make all these beautiful designs.  I had bought a compass and a protractor and would make a grid of evenly spaced dots and begin to make perfect circles with my compass,  making this flower fo lif! e pattern.  I occasionly  to this day will sit down and make f! lower of life.  Now, first encounter was around my dads birthday,  which was May 22 - I remember that much about the time frame.  I'm not absolutely sure of the exact date, but I would say it is accurate within a week either way. I didnt record the date of the first event. It just never occured to me to do so. I saw it at about 11:30 at night and my wife was asleep. I had stepped out on my back porch for a smoke,  which I did every night,  as I am some what of a night owl.  Standing on my back porch I had a greatly limited view of the sky,  as there were two giant oak trees,  one on each side of my view,  along with my garage/shed on my left and the house on my right.  I would say I could see about 1 percent of the sky from that spot.  As I stepped out and lit my smoke,  I noticed a very bright, large star directly in front me (It was due west), about twice as big as any star I had ever seen,  and much brighter than any star I had seen.  Initially I didn't give it a second glance,  ! which is odd because I was out there every night and never recalled seeing it before.  Well,  about halfway down my smoke I look up at the sky and noticed the large bright light again.  This time it caught my attention.  As I looked at the star,  I remember asking myself,  with my head slightly cocked and intense curiosity, "What is that?"   The next thing I remember thinking was that it looked like it was moving.  I stilled my head and squinted my eyes to maintain focus,  and sure enough it was moving very, very slowly and subtly to the right,  barely even noticable.  At this point I was hooked.  I became ignorant of everything around me and about me,  and anything else I might have been thinking on.   As I stared at this single bright light,  it began to seem like it was now getting lower in the sky,  then I noticed it was getting slightly larger and brighter.  I was frozen.  All my focus, energy, and intention was completely engulfed by this light.  In what seemed like s! econds,  the light's altitude in relation to the horizon was c! ut in ha lf.  The light became much larger and brighter and very clear,  with no glare, halo, or haze surrounding it.  It was at this point that I realized this light was descending and approaching me at a very fast rate.  At this point I had stepped out in the yard and had a much better scope of the sky,  including directly above me and back over the house a good way towards the east.  Once I realized this light was descending towards me,  it only took what seemed seconds for this flying craft to be directly over me at a very, very low altitude,  probably around 400-700 feet.  Now,  this craft had absolutely no sound signature,  except for a very low humming/vibratory effect that I felt more than heard.  Right before the ship was directly above me,  at some point I became oblivious of the large bright light that i guess was on the front of the ship,  and my full attention was shifted to the light display on the underbelly of the ship.  I'm really not quite sure how to explain this p! art,  for the under lights acted in a way that seemed more organic than artificial.  On approach,  I saw a mixture of red and yellow lights.  The lights reminded me of little seperated l.e.d.'s.  At this point I could make out a vague outline of the craft,  although I cant recall the exact shape for the lights had me somewhat "hypnotized", feeling very disoriented and confused as I watched the bewildering light show.  When I first saw the lights they seemed to be in a square pattern,  consisting of 15-20 individual red and yellow l.e.d.'s.  Now this is where it is hard to relate the account.  I cant think of any one word to accurately describe the action of the lights. While staring at the lights,  instantly,  with fluidity,  the lights were now in a circle shape,  with me never seeing any lights go out or new lights come on.  I never looked away,  as my exposure to the underlights was only about 10 -15 seconds long it seems.  The lights rolled or shifted,  or whatever you ! want to call it,  into two or three different patterns before ! it compl eted its low fly-over.  As it passed over the house,  it started its ascent and as quick as it approached it was gone,  first a farely bright light,  and gradually dissappearing within a minute or so.  I cannot describe the intensity of emotion that came upon me,  I was exhilerated.  I have never felt that quality of excitement up to that point.  I ran inside as fast as I could to try to wake my wife up,  shaking her and telling her I had just seen a UFO!!  She wouldnt wake up. I went back outside for a little bit before retiring.  I told her about it the next day.  She knew I had seen something,  but I think she thought I had just seen some kind of military aircraft or something else explainable.  The very next night,  as my wife and I sat inside our house,  she watching t.v. and me on the internet (probably researching the mayans,  as I had just gained knowledge of them and thus much interest),  I felt/heard the low humming vibration.  I looked at my wife wide-eyed and rem! ember exclaiming "THATS IT!!"  I ran outside just in time to see the ship ascending towards the east,  just as it did the previous night.  This is where I think my wife became convinced that I saw something,  for I described the event to her earlier that day,  describing the humming sensation it emitted,  and now she felt it too,  only she didnt make it outside in time to see it.  I was a bit bummed because I knew that without seeing it for herself,  she would never fully believe or appreciate the experience as I had.  The very next night,  for the third night in a row I heard the ship,  running out too late to see it.  Thats the first time. 
 
  SECOND EXPERIENCE  The second time was on Febuary 13 of 2008.   At this time we were living about 5 miles north,  with my wife's parents and her brother.  We could no longer afford the house in Union Grove due to the tremendous paycut I accepted by leaving Pepsi.   We moved in about July of '07.  After that first encounter,  I spent alot of time outside at night,  peering into the night sky,  looking for something else spectacular to happen.  Then one night it did,  and when I was least expecting it.  Right around 11:00 p.m., my wife and I had stepped out on the back porch of her parents house,  a medium sized commercially built log cabin with a covered wrap-around porch.  The back porch faced due west.  We had a 35-40 foot tree line for our horizon about 75 yards behind the house.  There was forest on both sides of the house,  so again our view was fairly limited.  We stepped out and approached the northwest corner of the house to smoke.  Thats also the corner of the house our ! bedroom was in.  As we turned and stopped, facing the backyard(west),   I remember noticing this incredibly bright looking star,  and upon recollection,  I remember thinking that it must be some planet,  but for some odd reason it didn't catch my interest initially,  which was abnormal for that season of my life.  The light was hovering,  as still as a star, for about the first five minutes we were out there,  just over the tree line.  Then my wife broke the silence,  inquiring seemingly to herself,  but out loud, "What is that?".   I responded, "What?",  not really sure what she was talking about.  She pointed at the bright light and said, "That,  what is that?".   As we stared at the light,  we almost immediately thought we noticed slight, slight movement.  At this point,  something clicked,  and I knew beyond a shadow of a doubt that this was the same thing I witnessed the previous May.  I remember putting my left arm on her right shoulder,  as I was to her right,  and j! umping up I shouted, "THATS IT, THATS IT!!".   I quickly ran i! nside to our bedroom to retrieve our camcorder,  which used mini cassette tapes.  I ran back outside stopping a few feet short of my wife,  who was now a couple of yards off the parch in the grass.  I looked up, and to my amazement I saw two very clear, large, bright lights descending out of the sky,  coming directly at us.  It was as though a giant car was floating in the sky,  as the lights were next to each other horizontally,  like headlights.  I tried to hold the camera in the direction I thought was correct,  for I was unable to pick up the lights on the fold out screen.  At this point I was repeatedly telling my wife,  "THATS IT,  THATS IT,  WATCH FOR THE LIGHTS,  WATCH FOR THE LIGHTS!!".  Less than a minute later the ship was passing directly over us,  slightly higher than the first time I seen it.  As the headlights were "out of view",   I say that because I never remember seeing the headligts go out,  its just like one second your looking at the white lights,  and the next! second all you see is the red and yellow lights underneath the object.  Just like the first time the red and yellow l "l.e.d.'s" became apparent,  and just like the first time they did their little "dance",  shifting from one obscure pattern to the next.  The humming sensation wasn't quite as noticable as it was the first time,  I assume because of its slight ly elevated altitude,  and I am quite sure that there were more red and yellow l.e.d.'s when I had seen it the first time.  It seems like this second time there were only around 10-12 lights displayed.  I was fascinated.  I'm thinking "what in the world is going on!!??"  The lights stayed visible for approximately 10-15 seconds,  just like the first time,  then it reascended and was gone in the east.  I couldn't hardly beleive it,  yet there it was.  My wife received first hand experience,  and it was like a huge weight was lifted,  because now I had somebody else who had seen it,  and could attest to the validity of ! my experience.  I recorded the date and the time that it happe! ned.  I' ll never forget it.  I checked the camcorder,  but for some reason nothing was recorded.  Im guessing the settings weren't ready for nighttime viewing. I was outside the next few nights,  but it didn't appear again.  I told many people close to me about the experience,  both family and friends,  including our three closest friends,  Brian whom I worked with at Pepsi and his wife Michelle,  and a bricklayer friend of mine name Joe.  However,  I could tell that nobody really thought we had seen anything "unusual",  with the exception of Michelle I think.  That would all change. 
 
  THIRD EXPERIENCE  The third encounter occurred on November 19 of 2008.  We had moved out of my in-laws house in April of '08.  I left my job as an EMT at the end of Feburary '08 in exchange for a job for a fellow named Al Ozment,  who owns USFoam,  a company contracted to put out coal mine fires in North America.  Mr. Ozment,  who previously was a firefighter in Oklahoma,  patented the process to effeciently extinguish fires in underground mines,  as well as recieving a patent for the formula of the foam that they used,  which they also manafactured.  I was offered a handsome salary,  much more than I made on the ambulance,  and a position putting out fires.  As it turned out,  he had only hired me to help finish a firetruck that he was going to enter into a show in Indiana,  firing me two months after hiring me,  after all the business with the show truck was done.  I returned to my EMT job,  getting re-employed that June with the same company that I had left that Febuary.  The s! ilver lining to that experience was that during that short time at USFoam,  one night while shopping at a local dollar store,  I ran into an old bricklayer friend,  Joe,   whom I had worked with in masonry out of high school.  We fell out of touch around '01,  and I had always wonderd where he was,  driving by where I knew he had last lived,  but with never any luck.  I feel that if I hadn't left the ambulance position,  my path would have turned out differently and I probably would have never ran into Joe.  We moved into a duplex in a town called *********, Tx,  about 8 miles south of my wifes parents house,  and only about 3 miles south of the house that we had lived in during the first experience.  Two duplexes down lived some friends fo ours,  Brian and his wife Michelle,  whom we had known since I had worked with him at Pepsi.  A few times I had poured my case out vohemently to Brian, Michelle, and Joe,  who all politely listened to me,  but afterwards would always try to convince me it was just some kind of manmade aircraft.  So now the stage is set.  There we all were,  all at my duplex on the evening of November 19.  It was around 10:30 or 11:00,  and I was heading to the backdoor of our place to join my wife Shelly,  and our friends Brian,  Michelle,  and Joe,  who were all already outside on the back porch.  My back door faces south and our neighbor we shared the duplex with is on the east side us,   As I stepped outside onto our small 8' by 8' concrete pad,  I took one step out,  and with my very next motio! n, for some reason,  i stretched my neck up and peered back up over the roof,  towards the front side of the house,  which faced north.  As I was doing this,  the other four were continuing to talk about whatever it was they were discussing.   Turning my gaze to the northern sky I immediately noticed a solid,  nonblinking light above the northwestern horizon of my rooftop,  which was the size and brightness of an average star in the sky,  that was moving east at a fairly moderate pace.  I was floored.  I shouted for evreyone to look.  Now we were all focused on this light moving steadily across the sky.  As the non-blinking light steadily moved east,  we noticed a couple of planes wiht their anti-collision lights blinking that appeated to be passing close to this object.  Then we see a much smaller steady red light that briefly appeared near the light.  As the light was now to our right(northeast) and getting close to being out of view,  it did something totally unexpected.! Instantly,  in the blink of an eye,  this solid white light ! was redu ced to about half the size and instead of white it was now a bright blue,  dissappearing completely in less than 2 seconds.  I was stunned.  It seemed that whatever it was moved across the sky at the same rate and distance,  and instantly moved very far away ver, very quickly.  As we all stood there,  staring at where the light used to be,  all of us simultaneously telling what we saw,  without even thinking about it,  I whipped my around to the left,  facing west,  while everybody else continued to look north/northeast.  Due west,  just above the power lines that ran down the next street over to the west of us,  was this huge cluster of individual yellowish orange lights,  kind of like this:  OOO OOOOO OOOOOOO OOOOO OOO    The pattern was more of a round shape,  with less of a linear arrangement than above,  more like a balanced matrix of lights, and I'm not sure exactly how many individual lights comprised the cluster,  but it was close to the number in the diagram.  I am standing in awe,   taken by this sight.  I remember,  almost in a dazed state,  asking everyone to look over here.  It was like someone had quickly erected some kind of stadium light over there.  My mind was wrestling to decipher what I was seeing.  Out of excitement I remember repeatedly saying,  "Ooh,  look over here,  look over here!!!"  We all stared frozen in awe.  Joe broke the silence by saying, "Aw,  thats some kind of tower."  I spent many nights outside and never had I seen the hovering cluster of lights,  so I knew that it wasn't any kind of tower.  I told Joe this.  The next thing I ! remember was noticing that the cluster looked like it was rising in the sky.  When I frist saw it it was very low in the sky,  just above the western horizon of the neighbors house,  just above the power lines.  The lights rose for about 20 or 30 seconds.  As it rose it never dimmed or brightened,  nor did it get any bigger or smaller,  which I guess means that it was going straight up,  slightly towards us as it rose.  After it reached its apex,  it starting gradually getting bigger,  as though it was descending towards us.   It isnt realy clear when or how,  but at some point after we noticed it descending,  I dont remember seeing the cluster lights,  but instead two fixed, white,  non-blinking lights on what initialy appeared to be wing tips,  and one single red light,  non-blinking as well,  in the middle of the two white lights,  all appearing to be on the underside of some type of craft coming right at us.  Somehow I knew at this point what it was.  I remember falling! to my knees,  staring into the sky the whole time,  yelling, ! "Thats I t,  Thats It,  Watch for the lights, Watch the lights,  Watch the lights!!!".  As it approached us at an altitude very close to the altitude it was the first time I had seen it,  the fixed lights seemed to become unnoticable,  and the single red light in the center underneath was now joined with many other single little red and yellow lights,  just like the other encounters.  Just like the other visitations the lights did their little shifting "dance",  doing patterns different than the ones it did the first two times.  Also there wasn't near as many lights this time,  maybe 10 all together.  The same humming/vibratory effect was present.  As we all watched this pass over our heads,  no one said a word,  except me maybe,  I do know I was very excited and remember repeatedly yelling, "Watch the lights!!".  It passed directly overhead,  slowly started its ascent and within a minute it was gone,  completely out of sight.  Now they believed.  No three night flyby this time eithe! r.  It was just on the 19th.  I remember a couple of nights later,  for some reason I started thinking about the dates of the encounters,  and began wondering if maybe there was a pattern.  What I discovered was that each time I saw the "ship",  it was on a half moon.  I measured the days and found out that it is exactly nine moon cycles between each half-moon occurence.  Then,  just recently,  I started thinking on the fact that I had never heard of a UFO case like mine and began researching UFO reports and cases.  I decided that I could use a fresh perspective,   and I would much like to hear what you think. 
 
 
((NUFORC Note:  Witness indicates that date is approximate.  PD))

summary: A ball, bright as an LED, 15 feet away from us, stayed infront of our car for about 10 seconds at 110MPH then disappear in the horizon
stats: Occurred : 3/17/2012 23:50  (Entered as : 03/17/2012 11:50 PM) Reported: 11/11/2022 6:52:12 AM 06:52 Posted: 12/22/2022 Location: Near Eva, OK Shape: Sphere Duration: 15 seconds Characteristics: There were lights on the object
text:
A ball, bright as an LED, 15 feet away from us, stayed infront of our car for about 10 seconds at 110MPH then disappear in the horizon 
 
My wife and myself, in 2012, were driving from Santa Fe, NM to Oklahoma city, on a road trip around the US. 
When we saw the UFO, it was close to mid night. 
 
It was on Road 412 in OK, I remember because my old Garmin GPS was on, as we do not live in that area and we relied on it to make it to our destinations. 
 
This is a road with almost no traffic, it is a VERY LONG, STRAIGHT, one lane each-way road. (see google maps) 
 
I was driving on cruise control at about 110MPH. I was young and reckless, but the weather was nice, and I had really good visibility. 
 
All of the sudden, a bright, white ball, showed up out of no where, it came from behind us, in a bit of a diagonal direction, meaning, it came from the direction of my right side back, and stayed in front of me, slightly to my left at about 12 feet from the ground and about 15 feet from us. 
 
It kept a steady distance from our car, so from our reference point, it seemed to remain in a steady position, meaning, it was traveling at around 110MP, it didn't wobble, did not go up or down, it didn't make a sound, it just stayed fixated in the same position and distance from my car. 
 
10 seconds later, it just accelerated from the position it was in, with reference to my car moving at 110MP, to the horizon. That distance was covered in 1 second. It didn't go up, to the sky, it went straight, keeping more or less the same height. 
 
This road has no lights, no main cities nearby, it was not a star we saw high up in the sky, it was very close to us, it was not the reflection of my headlights in the electrical cables that follows the road, this road has no elevation, no turns, no traffic, just a boring straight long road. 
 
I am an engineer, I look for explanations for the things I see, this was not an hallucination, we were not under the influence, it truly is what we saw. 
 
Nothing happened to our car, our electrical systems, our vision, everything kept a normal condition, other than us being shaken up. 
 
I only filed this today because I just found out about this site from a Shotime show.

text:
Began as a bright blue ball of light and then a triangle craft with a bright white light coming from the inner front of craft 
 
My husband, daughter and I were on our way home. We were on Roundtop Rd and just about to Church Ave.when we noticed a bright glowing blue ball to the right of us in the sky. It seemed like it was just haphazardly falling out of the sky. I told my husband who was driving that we should go try to find it as it could be a meteorite. He said no that it could be miles away and it was dusk and that we were going home. When we got home about 2 minutes later, we walked to the back door to go in the house. I noticed a bright white light in the south part of our field coming north. It was really low and despite how cold it was, we decided to hang out and see what this was approaching. It took about 10 minutes to get to us. It was going very slow and staying at tree top height. Which was very low as we are in a valley. It made no sound at all. It was dead silent. It was black with a red light on the middle of the under carriage and each of the angles had a gold light. The white light that we saw was coming from inner window of the front of the craft. I would have to say it was as large as a small home. It went past us going maybe 10mph as we watched in amazement. After we watched it go north and disappear we went in the house to get changed. While I was upstairs getting my pajamas on I heard a loud whirring sound. I looked out the window and there were 2 maybe 3 great big what looked like military choppers flying low with red lights on them.They flew towards where the craft was seen when we got home and then minutes later they flew in the same direction the craft had flew in before we couldn't see it anymore. We have no military bases nearby. We didn't talk about or tell anyone about this until 2015. I feel that the blue ball and this craft were the same.

The most stunning aspect of the experience for me was the way the formation seemed to sense that I had noticed it because it kind of ‚Äúflinched‚Äù the moment I spotted it as if it didnt want to be seen and began evasive maneuvers. summary: I've reported my sighting here before but I didn't tell the whole story and I wanted to update it. I can give better details on phone
stats: Occurred : 6/14/2015 01:00  (Entered as : 06/14/2015 1:00 AM) Reported: 12/6/2022 9:26:06 PM 21:26 Posted: 12/22/2022 Location: Beeville, TX Shape: Light Duration: 5 - 10 minutes Characteristics: There was an aura or haze around the object, The object emitted other objects, The object emitted beams
text:
I've reported my sighting here before but I didn't tell the whole story and I wanted to update it. I can give better details on phone 
 
.June 14, 2015 had some chase me down the highway in Beeville, Texas. Was doing 70mph, at first it was just one flying in front of me directly over the road, it then circled around my truck and came up from behind me, I looked out to the side of my truck and realized the whole area was lit up, I was to scared to look up to see how close it was above me. I hit the gas and spead up, it then circled back in front of me, it crossed the road and suddenly blinked super fast 7 or 8 times, when it finished it disappeared for four seconds and then a new one appeared and copied the same super fast blinking 7-8 times, now there was two of em. This whole time they were maybe 50 ft in the air and 75 - 100 ft in front of me, mind u this whole time I was doing 70mph, it's like they were able to lock speed with me. They were the same size, randomly moving around, off and on blinking. After a few miles they slowly started going up higher and higher directly above the road. I was finally able to pass em, and eventually lost sight of em. Then a few miles down the road I saw a group of three of em flying parallel with the road heading south and I was heading north. These were about 100 yards from the road on the lefthand side of road. These were different sizes a LG, med, sm and they flew in a tight triangle formation and it wasn't a perfect triangle the bottom left was the smallest and was flying a little closer to the top one which was the largest. It reminded me of whales and dolphins how you see the babies swim just underneath the parents. They flew 15 - 20 ft above the trees and they were shining down a beam of light as they flew, I could see the tree tops light up as they flew. When they got directly parallel with me, I looked away, because I got scared that they were going to pick up on my sense that I was nearby. I looked forward waited a few seconds then did a quick turnaround and looked just to make sure that they had kept going, and hadn't started following me. They were about the size of a soccer ball, cantaloupe and a softball. I eventually made it to a gas station all I wanted to do was tell people what I just saw but I knew I better just keep my mouth shut. I looked up sightings for that city and realized there have been many similar sightings over the years. I kinda developed ptsd from it for about a year, would have dreams about it and can't help but constantly looking at the sky while driving at nighttime. Forgot to mention that all the lights were white and super bright. And the first two I saw were the same size.

summary: A land-based unidentified object; ethereal, shape-changing, and moving in an apparent orderly manner across 50 feet
stats: Occurred : 8/19/2015 00:00  (Entered as : 08/19/2015 12:00 AM) Reported: 10/18/2022 5:13:38 PM 17:13 Posted: 12/22/2022 Location: Newton, MA Shape: Changing Duration: 5 minutes
text:
A land-based unidentified object; ethereal, shape-changing, and moving in an apparent orderly manner across 50 feet 
 
Just a note - I'm an engineer with a graduate degree and a I'm generally a rational person. I was not under the influence of anything when I observed this and was in good health. I viewed this object from a second-floor bedroom window to ground level on a dark night. No reflective surfaces were nearby. Object was 2-1/2 to 3 feet long, perhaps 6-7" wide on average, mostly oblong, transparent white with amorphous "fuzzy" borders. Its motion was generally slow and steady and it was moving along shrubbery/plants with occasional pauses. I wondered if my eyes were not focusing and if it was some kind of whitish rabbit or mink, which would have been highly unusual but not out of the question, but then its shape altered, kind of how a bubble alters as it's being blown from a wand, if that makes sense; it's size did not change appreciably. After moving along the garden, it came toward the house along a perpendicular line (for the most part.) Once it came close enough I could no longer see it; I went downstairs to ground level and did not see it. I returned upstairs and it was no longer in view. It is hard to describe how it moved, but when I went snorkeling recently, I realized the movement of fish along a coral reef was strikingly similar. So I don't know if it was actually on the ground per se, or perhaps just above it.

summary: Mirror-like cigar shaped craft slowed to a stop above us, rotated and then climbed in altitude so fast it was gone in a moment.
stats: Occurred : 2/15/2017 19:30  (Entered as : 02/15/2017 7:30 PM) Reported: 12/14/2022 9:01:38 PM 21:01 Posted: 12/22/2022 Location: Seattle, WA Shape: Cigar Duration: 60 seconds Characteristics: Animals reacted to the event
text:
Mirror-like cigar shaped craft slowed to a stop above us, rotated and then climbed in altitude so fast it was gone in a moment. 
 
My partner at the time and I were walking home with our dog after taking her out to go to the bathroom before heading to bed. We lived in an apartment by the Hiram M. Chittenden Locks in the Ballard neighborhood of Seattle, WA. We were facing SW, towards the direction of the ocean. 
 
At first I thought I was seeing a biplane with no lights on flying way too close to the city - but it made no sound. I opened my mouth and pointed at it to my partner and as I did so it began moving in a way that didn‚Äôt make sense if it were a biplane. I remember asking what the heck is this at that point. 
 
Silent and mirror-like. The color of the craft was so stealth it was as if it reflected the night sky around it. You could almost say like it moved as if it was not even in the same night sky. It was just so quiet for how big it was and as much as it was definitely there it was also very difficult to really ‚Äúsee‚Äù it. However I also think that could be an effect from the perceptual dissonance of seeing such a huge flying craft so close with an utter lack of sound. I‚Äôd never seen anything like this. Complete mindf***. 
 
My partner quickly saw it as well. We had very much an ‚Äúoh s***‚Äù moment as it came from what looked like over the ocean, maybe 500ft in the air, crossed half a mile NE and dropped down to a stop about 100ft above us. 
 
Me, my partner and even my dog were staring at this thing for possibly 10-15 seconds as it stopped and slowly rotated like a football being spun on the ground. Then just as soon as we were able to register what was happening and that something phenomenally out of the ordinary was above us, it began to raise in altitude and as fast as it started - it was over. Couldn‚Äôt have taken more than 3 seconds to completely disappear into the night sky.

summary: 5 large perfectly circular white lights in a triangle shape, dark triangle silhouette behind lights, slow and close overhead no sound.
stats: Occurred : 10/6/2018 23:30  (Entered as : 10/06/2018 11:30 PM) Reported: 10/15/2022 9:30:52 PM 21:30 Posted: 12/22/2022 Location: Round Top, TX Shape: Triangle Duration: 3-5 Minutes Characteristics: There were lights on the object
text:
5 large perfectly circular white lights in a triangle shape, dark triangle silhouette behind lights, slow and close overhead no sound. 
 
I was sitting outside The Stone Cellar at a fire pit located near the building. I looked up and saw 5 large perfectly circular white lights in a triangle shape, with a dark triangle silhouette behind the lights. Each light was very large, at least 15-20 feet in diameter and emitted a soft, not harsh light, if I had not been looking at it directly I might not have noticed it. It was a light similar to that of the moon. It passed slow and close overhead with no sound, about 30 yards from the top of the Stone Cellar building (the building is an old train station, single story). I watched it for about 3-5 minutes as it slowly passed over my head and continued away from the building , South East, towards the center of town (Round Top town hall area). It seemed like it either quickly zoomed away or blinked off its lights at the end of my view. , it was hard to tell. Once it was gone I asked other people who had been inside/ on the patio of the building if they saw anything but no one had, I was the only one who witnessed this phenomenon at the time. While I was at a bar, I was sober as I was a designated driver and I do not drink alcohol as part of my belief system. I am currently a graduate student and AmerCorps service member.

summary: Plus signs with lights on each tip moving erratically
stats: Occurred : 4/13/2019 23:25  (Entered as : 04/13/2019 11:25 PM) Reported: 10/13/2022 7:08:51 PM 19:08 Posted: 12/22/2022 Location: Bartlett, IL Shape: Cross Duration: Hour-ish Characteristics: There were lights on the object, There were aircraft in the vicinity or aircraft chasing the object
text:
Plus signs with lights on each tip moving erratically 
 
(Disclaimer: This is an old story from when I was in high school, I've since moved away. I still remember it like it was yesterday. I have several videos but will not put them online as part of them takes place at my house) My friends and I were driving around and saw a strange aircraft, a cross shape with rounded ends like two popsicle sticks. There was a white light on each end. It flew straight, stopped in midair and hovered, then flew another direction without turning. We tried following it, but we noticed a lot of helicopters in the sky including one that seemed to always be going the same way we were, so we grew anxious and gave up the chase. We witnessed the aircraft again (or a different one) near the intersection of Bartlett & 59, and this time it was doing flips in the air. About the size of a 747 or something but definitely not a plane. It would rotate upside down (if it even had a sense of 'upside down'), fly around, stop on a dime, go a different direction, go straight up or straight down while parallel to the ground, a lot of different things. It flew off to the north and we gave up following. Then we saw another one on Struckman Blvd near Sunrise Park. It was the most active, doing barrel rolls and all the actions described above. It was also lower in the sky, so we got a sense of how big it was. As we headed home, suddenly the sky was full of big passenger planes (Boeings and such) flying extremely low with bright lights on, so bright they functioned as spotlights on the ground and too low to realistically land anywhere except the small local airport (though that was in a different direction). Obviously they didn't crash, but it seemed like they were looking for something.
